title: sausage cheese loaf
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Cook sausage until crisp and drain well.
Mix cheese and sausage together.
Put in loaf pan that
has
been sprayed with Pam.
Let set in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Remove from pan and slice.
Serve with crackers, toast or thin sliced French bread.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: First slice luncheon meat in half; spread cream cheese 1/4-inch thick.
Add 1 or 2 pieces of jalapenos.
Roll up.
Keep chilled until serving time.

title: grandma's stuffing
directions: Cut up celery and onions; saute.
Mix all ingredients.
If you do not have enough turkey broth, add some milk.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rudolph sandwiches
directions: Cut a large triangle out of bread.
Cover bread with peanut butter.
Place raisins for eyes, cherry for his nose and whole and broken pretzels for antlers.
After seeing your creation, enjoy. Children can make these.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Chop dates, orange slices and nuts into small pieces. Roll in about 1 cup of the flour. Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Add remaining flour alternately with milk. Blend in nuts, coconut, candy and dates. Pour into greased tube pan. Cook in a 250° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: kentucky wonder pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and egg whites.
Beat well, then add nuts, then fold in egg whites.
Pour in greased tube pan and bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Needs no icing.

title: crab dip
directions: Cream ingredients.
Spread on a serving dish.
Top with jar of cocktail sauce and then layer crab meat.

title: creamy cheddar corn and broccoli
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Remove 1/2 cup and mix with nuts for topping.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat sugar into slightly beaten eggs.
Add flavoring and nutmeg.
Scald 2 cups milk.
Pour slowly into eggs.
Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: kariann's sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, oats, milk, onions, pepper and salt.
Mix well. Shape into about 30 small balls.
Brown in hot shortening. Drain.
Combine catsup, worcestershire sauce, sugar and water. Mix well.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer 30 minutes covered over low heat.

title: shake and bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl and stir to combine. Use 6 to 8 pieces or 2 pounds boneless chicken breast.

title: ambrosia balls
directions: Melt over low heat; cool.
Roll into balls or drop by spoonful.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in pot you are going to make the soup in.
Add onion, carrots and celery; saute over low heat until soft.
Add flour and cornstarch; cook until bubbly.
Add stock and milk and make smooth sauce.
Add soda and grated cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add parsley, a few minutes before serving.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix until melted and smooth.
While still over low heat, add vanilla, cocoa and powdered sugar.
Remove from stove and mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Press into pan.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: turkey pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions, rinse in cold water.
Separate broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together with dressing.
Serve.

title: pineapple ice cream
directions: Combine the evaporated milk, pudding mix, crushed pineapple and beaten egg in top of a double boiler and cook over hot water until mixture coats a spoon.
Cooking is recommended because it is not advisable to eat raw eggs.

title: french fish fillets
directions: Dip fish in French dressing, then in crumbs.
Place in a greased, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and cover with waxed paper.
Microwave 4 to 6 minutes, turning dish after 2 1/2 minutes.

title: macaroni salmon salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine macaroni, salmon, celery and onion.
Blend mayonnaise, liquid smoke and salt; toss lightly with salmon mixture.
Chill; garnish with parsley.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook the broccoli; drain well.
Cut into spears or flowerets.
Arrange in a single layer in a two-quart ovenproof dish.
Lay pieces of chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine rest of ingredients and spoon over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pasta soup
directions: Use 4-quart pan.
In saucepan, cook sausage (take casing off) and onion.
Drain grease.
Add all other ingredients, except pasta, in pan.
Bring to a boil, then add pasta.
Turn down heat and simmer until pasta is tender.

title: gail's banana nut bread
directions: Combine butter and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture, alternating after each addition.
Add nuts; mix.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, chilies and chicken in large bowl.
Put tablespoon sauce on each tortilla and pinch of cheese.
Put 1 dozen in each 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour leftover sauce generously over each pan.
Cover all tortillas.
Sprinkle leftover cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
It is done when bubbling.
Serve cut in half.
Makes 48.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt.
Wash rice	and
arrange on bottom of casserole and put chicken on top
of
rice with skin side up. Add soup and water.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or until chicken
is
brown.
Cover with foil
and	cook
until chicken and rice are tender and sauce thickened.
If
rice	is dry, add a little water.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: hot egg salad sandwiches
directions: Split hamburger buns and spread split side with a layer of deviled ham.
Top with a thin slice of onion, 1 scrambled egg and a layer of grated American cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with butter/margarine or nonstick cooking spray.
Prepare stuffing mix according to directions.
Dice chicken.
(Note:
You may use leftover cooked chicken or use 2 pounds of boiled chicken breast.) Layer 1/2 of stuffing in casserole dish.
Spread chicken over stuffing and add the remaining stuffing over diced chicken.
Dilute soup with 1/4 cup water and heat until smooth.
Pour warm soup over casserole and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Slice cabbage in chunks.
Cook in salt water until tender and drain.
Mix soup, milk and cheese; pour over cabbage.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides. Grease casserole well. Place 1 tablespoon rice for each pork chop in bottom. Place chops on rice. Place slice onion, tomato and pepper on each chop. Cover with chicken broth; bake for 1 hour at 350°. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together first six ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and toss to coat well.
Cover. Chill.
Makes five cups.

title: "ashley's favorite parmesan chicken"
directions: Melt butter and set aside.
Salt, pepper, garlic salt and garlic pepper chicken thighs.
Dip in melted butter and then in cheese/crumb mixture.
Roll up chicken and place in a baking dish. Sprinkle with leftover crumb mixture, if any.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until golden brown.
Serve with a nice Caesar salad, pasta and garlic bread.

title: barbecued beef sandwiches
directions: Place stew beef meat in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour ginger ale and chili sauce over.
Stir.
Bake in oven, uncovered, at 350° until fork-tender (approximately 2 to 2 1/2 hours).
To prevent tops of meat pieces from burning, you need to stir the mixture at about 30 minute intervals.
When tender and sauce has thickened, remove from oven.
Shred meat with 2 forks or use food processor, if desired.
Serve on buns.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; let cool.
Stir in honey, buttermilk, pumpkin and eggs.
Combine flour and remaining ingredients; make a well in center of mixture.
Add pumpkin mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake. (Batter can be refrigerated up to 3 days.)
To bake, spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: golden corn and broccoli casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
In a 3-quart saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add cleaned and cut up broccoli.
Return water to a boil.
Cover saucepan and reduce heat to low.
Cook 8 minutes or until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Drain in colander.
In the same saucepan, stir soup, milk, cheese and pepper together.
Return broccoli to saucepan and heat mixture over medium heat.
Pour into prepared casserole.
Bake uncovered casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients, except the kisses.
Mix at low speed until dough forms.
Shape dough into small balls, using a rounded teaspoonful.
Roll each ball in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet; top each cookie with a chocolate kiss. Allow to cool.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Tear rolls in half.
Melt margarine.
Empty container of Parmesan cheese in Ziploc bag.
Dip roll halves in melted butter; put in bag of Parmesan cheese and shake.
Put on cookie sheet. Brown in 350° oven.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Crush candy bars and set aside. Pinch half of cake into small pieces, put in bowl. Mix milk, sugar and egg yolks together. Cook over double broiler stirring constantly until thick. Add butter and powdered sugar to previous mixture. Fold in whipped topping; mix until creamy. Put 1/2 on cake; use 1/2 candy bars. Repeat process. Keep refrigerated.

title: "longwood tearoom" lemon bisque
directions: Whip canned milk until stiff.
Add sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind, beating good.
Sprinkle vanilla wafer crumbs in bottom of freezer dish of tray.
Pour lemon mixture on top of crumbs. Sprinkle a few crumbs on top of lemon.
Place in freezer until firm.

title: modesto chicken
directions: Mix the teriyaki sauce with barbecue sauce.
Add garlic. Marinate chicken overnight in mixture, then grill using the leftover mixture to baste the chicken.

title: brownie torte
directions: Butter and flour a 9-inch round cake pan.
In saucepan, heat butter and corn syrup until butter is melted.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add sugar and eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in vanilla, flour and nuts.
Pour batter into pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until center springs back when touched. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out of pan onto a rack.

title: sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage, onion, garlic and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are soft.
Pour on cooked elbow macaroni or other small pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bake in preheated oven at 450° until golden brown.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix everything.
Roll it out.
Cut and bake in a hot oven (350°).

title: fish dish
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut fish into 1-inch serving size pieces.
Put fish in bottom of dish.
Pour soup over top of fish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes; stir.
Add cheese and crackers over top, then bake for 20 minutes more.

title: earth day dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos in food processor.
Cream together butter, sugar and cream cheese.
In separate bowl, mix together milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Alternate layers of mixture and cookie crumbs in a large flowerpot or individual ones, starting and ending with cookie crumbs.
Chill or freeze.

title: lamb curry with cabbage
directions: Rinse lamb.
Combine yogurt, garlic, ginger, coriander, cloves, cinnamon, mace, cardamom and salt.
Marinate lamb in mixture for at least 4 hours or overnight.
Melt 1 stick of butter in a Dutch oven.
Add onions and saute until lightly browned.
Add lamb and marinade.
Cover and simmer over low heat without adding water for 1/2 hour.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Remove center of a 1-pound round pumpernickel bread and fill with dip.
Cube another 1-pound half and half bread for serving with dip.

title: dreamy chocolate mint sauce(15 minutes)
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, butter, water and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil (5 to 8 minutes).
Boil 3 minutes; remove from heat.
Immediately add chocolate chips; beat with a wire whisk or rotary beater until smooth.
Stir in creme de menthe. Serve warm or cool over ice cream or cake.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: chicken thighs a la low calories
directions: Select chicken thighs and place in T-Fal roaster or skillet.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place dough into 4 long rectangles.
In ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan, press over bottom and 1-inch up on sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: fudge pie
directions: Press into pie plate.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Whip egg whites on medium speed until soft peaks form. Continue on medium speed while gradually adding sugar and baking powder.
Continue whipping until very stiff peaks form and all sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Add saltines and pecans; gently fold in by hand.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, until center is almost firm. Remove from oven and cool upside down.
When cooled, top with whipping cream and pecans.

title: tiny party puffs
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add butter or margarine, stirring until melted.
Add flour and salt all at once.
Stir well until mixture is smooth and forms a soft ball.
Cool mixture slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
After last addition, continue beating until mixture is shiny.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet to make 36 small puffs.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Allow to cool in a warm place away from drafts.
When cool, fill with shrimp or salmon salad. Decorate with parsley or softened cream cheese in a flower design. Yields 36 Tiny Party Puffs.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with mixer. Add apples and pecans. Stir with a spoon until mixed well. Bake on 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown meat
and
onions;
add salt and pepper to taste. Prepare cornbread
mix
as per instructions on box.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake.
On top of cornbread mixture, spread cooked meat, then two cans of creamed corn.
Cover evenly with grated cheese.
Bake
at
375° for 30 minutes, then cover with foil and cook another 15 minutes so cheese does not burn.

title: jello salad
directions: Place gelatin in bowl.
Drain fruit.
Heat 2/3 cup juice and pour over gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add lemon juice and cheese, stirring until well blended.
Add fruits and undrained pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in cream which has been whipped stiff.
Chill.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted margarine and 2 eggs.
Pat in the bottom of a "Pammed" sheet cake pan.
Mix together confectioners sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs and vanilla and pour over top if first layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cake will sink in the middle.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Chop the first 4 ingredients.
Spread with grated cheese (one's choice).
Mix vinegar, sugar, oil, mustard and onion.
Pour over ingredients.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: clam dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients with softened cream cheese by hand or in mixer until creamy.

title: chicken-sausage jambalaya
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until rice is done.

title: semi-sweet oatmeal cookies
directions: Start heating oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Blend together the butter, sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in oats and chocolate pieces.
Drop rounded 1/2 teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: veal or chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound meat to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place 1 slice each of ham and cheese on each piece of meat.
Roll carefully, beginning at narrow end.
Secure with wooden picks.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and allspice; coat rolls with flour mixture.
Dip in egg; roll in crumbs.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add rolls and cook until brown. Add water and heat to boiling.
Cover.
Simmer until meat is tender, adding water if necessary, about 45 minutes.
Remove cover during last few minutes to crisp meat slightly.

title: swedish cocktail meatballs
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine beef, sausage, bread crumbs, egg, 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper and 1/8 teaspoon nutmeg.
Mix thoroughly and set aside.
In large skillet, melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Add onion and celery.
Cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Stir into meat mixture.
Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
In large skillet, melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter.
Add meatballs and cook over medium heat until firm and golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.

title: fish chowder
directions: Dice salt pork and saute in soup kettle until very crisp. Remove salt pork and set aside.
Dice onions and saute in fat; do not brown.
Add diced potatoes.
Wash fish and place in kettle. Cover fish, onions and potatoes with cold water.
Add salt, pepper and sauce.
Cook until fish flakes, about 30 minutes.
Add heated milk.
Sprinkle salt pork on top of chowder.
Serve with oyster crackers or tea biscuits.
Yields 8 servings.

title: oriental rice
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter in medium saucepan.
Add water and bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables and soy sauce.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until all water is absorbed.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Take 1/2 stick butter, saute onion in this.
Pan-fry sauerkraut in other 1/2 stick of butter until soft.
Cook lasagna noodles al dente.
Make mashed potatoes according to package directions for 6 to 8 servings.

title: "extra special" strawberry pie
directions: Combine and press ingredients into 10-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove and let cool.

title: chocolate apple candies
directions: Combine chocolate chips, applesauce and almond extract in a saucepan.
Heat and stir until chocolate chips are melted. Blend in sugar, cherries and nuts.
Chill until firm (approximately 1 hour). Shape into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: beef meat pie
directions: Dice potatoes.
Fry onions, but do not brown them.
Brown hamburger.
Combine hamburger, onions, potatoes, bouillon cubes, spices and water.
Simmer for 90 minutes on low heat.
Make sure all water evaporates.
Pack meat mixture into pie shell and dust with crushed cloves.
Cover with top shell.
Make 6 or 8 slits in middle of top shell and bake at 350° until brown .

title: stuffed celery sticks
directions: Cut celery into 3-inch pieces (be sure it's dry).
Mix remaining ingredients; spread about 1 tablespoon in each piece of celery.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cream butter spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Combine potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream and onion powder.
Whip until fluffy, adding a little milk if necessary.
Spread in buttered 13 x 9-inch dish or pan. Refrigerate or freeze until needed.
When ready to bake, drizzle melted margarine over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 15.

title: citrus fruit salad
directions: Peel and section the grapefruit and the oranges.
Put fruit in bowl; sprinkle the Equal over it.
Stir.
Any fruit can be added, also, nuts and marshmallows.

title: marinade for steaks
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over thick steaks to be broiled or barbecued.
Marinate 2 hours at room temperature.
Pat the steak dry with paper towel after draining and before cooking.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Spray bundt pan with Pam and sprinkle with sugar.
Shake off excess sugar.
Pour mixture into pan, and bake at 325 degrees to 350 degrees until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes to one hour.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften all cheeses at room temperature for several hours, then mash them together.
Then mix with mixer.
Add onion, horseradish and Miracle Whip.
Mix together well.
Roll into two large balls or three smaller ones.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ground meat; mix well.
Add ground meat; mix thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Drain, if necessary.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: darn good chocolate cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Then fold in chips.
Pour into prepared bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and margarine; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add milk alternately with flour and other dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 2 pans and bake at 350° until done (approximately 25 to 30 minutes).
Frost with your favorite chocolate icing.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Marinate sirloin in 1 teaspoon cornstarch, sherry, soy sauce, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon oil, pepper and garlic for 1 hour.
Heat in remaining oil in wok on high.
Stir-fry meat.
Remove.
Mix remaining starch with oyster sauce.
Stir-fry broccoli and carrots for 30 seconds; add broth.
Cover wok and steam for 1 minute or until vegetables are tender but retain crunch.
Add corn, peas, scallion, beef and sauce mix.
Heat until clear and thickened. Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Cream butter.
Stir in sour cream.
Gradually add Bisquick. Stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Spoon mixture into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Small muffin pan works best.
You will want to make a double batch of these.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar, 4 eggs and vanilla; set aside.
In another bowl mix plain flour, whipped oatmeal, salt, baking powder, soda and chocolate chips.
Form into small balls, place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until edges are brown.

title: hamburger roast
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into chunks.
Boil until tender.
Mash and leave to cool.
Combine mashed potatoes, ground beef and all other ingredients, except bacon.
Mix well and shape into thick, rectangular loaf.
Wrap slices of bacon around hamburger roast, tucking ends under loaf.
Place in roasting pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Serves 10.

title: cold water cake
directions: Grease pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Melt chocolate, butter and sugar and set aside. Cream together Crisco and 1 1/2 cups sugar; add well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift together 3 times, flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add all to mixture with 1 cup cold water, you can use layer cake pan or sheet.

title: apple snack cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon and salt.
Beat well. Add flour and soda.
Blend in apples and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool.
Top with powdered sugar.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle onion, cheese and bacon over bottom of pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth in blender on high speed or one minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown or knife inserted in middle comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate remaining pie.
Makes 6 servings.

title: margaret bradbury's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in casserole.
Put a package corn flakes and 1/2 cup smoked slivered almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Add margarine on top.

title: extra good cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage into quarters.
Allow to stand in cold water 1 hour.
Drain.
Shred fine, cover with the following dressing.
Mix flour, sugar and mustard and set aside.
Bring one cup water to boil, add vinegar and oil, add dry ingredients.
Mash egg yolks with dressing.
Chop egg whites with cabbage.
Pour dressing over and season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: uncle bob's stewed tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over medium heat until tomatoes reach desired thickness.
Makes two quarts.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and flavorings together, add to dry ingredients and beat 15 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Nuts may be added to the batter.

title: apple salad dressing
directions: Blend together and cook sugar, flour and salt.
In cup beat egg and add cream; then add vinegar and mustard.
Mix all of the ingredients together and cook until clear.
Dice up several apples and pour dressing over them.
Pecans may be added.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a large bowl, add melted butter, creamed corn, whole kernel corn, corn muffin mix and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Left over easy to freeze.
May be microwaved later and used.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender. Blend well and serve.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Roll pieces of meat in mixture of flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown in oil.
Add chopped onions and brown a few minutes longer.
Sprinkle any remaining flour over meat; stir. Add hot water, enough to just cover meat.
Cover; simmer 2 hours or until almost tender.
Add vegetables, except peas, and cook for 35 minutes longer.
Add peas and cook 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar and fold in pumpkin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Then roll up and let cool.
Unroll and add filling.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Blend all together on medium-high for 2 minutes or until well blended.
Grease pan very well.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: beef roll
directions: Treat beef with instant meat tenderizer following label directions.
Combine next 6 ingredients; spread on steak.
Roll up jelly roll fashion; fasten with string.
Brown in hot fat. Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Add water to cover bottom of pan.
Cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours.
Add more water during cooking if necessary.
Serves 4.

title: chile corn chowder
directions: In a large, heavy pot, brown sausage (may use ham, chicken or kielbasa) and onion.
Use oil, if necessary.
Drain fat.
Add potatoes, carrots and celery.
Add enough water to cover.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add corn, chiles and milk.
Heat and serve.
Thicken with instant mashed potato flakes, if necessary. Hearty winter meal!

title: blueberry salad
directions: Stir Jell-O in boiling water until dissolved.
Add fruit and nuts.
Let congeal for several hours.
Whip sour cream and cream cheese and pour over firm Jell-O mixture.
Garnish with extra nuts.

title: rice dressing
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic in small amount of oil (2 tablespoons).
Brown meat.
Add 2 cups water. Bring to a boil. Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Add roux (commercial) or make in separate pan, using 2 tablespoons oil and 2 tablespoons flour.
Stir until desired brownness.
Add cooked rice, salt and pepper.

title: forever amber
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in floured, greased pan (9 x 13-inch) and bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat 8 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and stir gently to mix.
Spoon into 3-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and drain.
Mix in 1/2 stick margarine and cheese.
Put in casserole.
Melt other 1/2 stick margarine with crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over broccoli.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: In a soup pot, melt the 2 tablespoons of butter and add onion; saute on medium heat until onion is tender.
Add milk, half and half and the stick of butter.
Stir until butter melts, then add salt, pepper, celery seed and dry mustard, stirring until well blended.
Add mashed potatoes, then chopped potatoes.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Soup is ready to serve when potatoes are fork-tender (about an hour).
Makes six 1-cup servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops and remove from skillet.
Add chopped onion and saute.
Add all the other ingredients to onions in skillet, except pork chops.
Pour into casserole dish and place browned pork chops on top.
Cover and bake until rice is done at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda together. Beat shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour-nut mixture with mashed bananas, small amount at a time; beat well. Turn into greased pan and bake in medium oven, at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until done.
Makes 1 loaf.
Bake at 325° for a glass pan.

title: bandana muffins(banana-oatmeal muffins)
directions: Cream together bananas, margarine, eggs and honey with electric hand mixer.
Mix together in separate bowl the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt, then stir into banana mixture.
Add the oats and stir until blended.
Grease or spray muffin tins.
Fill each 3/4 full.
They don't rise much.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm with butter.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all and mix.
Chill about 4 hours before serving. Will stay in refrigerator a week to 10 days.
Serve with a dollop of sour cream.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and scald; remove from heat. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Cool to lukewarm; add eggs and yeast mixture.
Beat in 3 cups of flour; allow mixture to rise in a warm place (85°) for 30 minutes.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Mix meat, onion flakes, garlic and cheese in pie plate.
Place remaining ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat with an electric mixer until smooth.
Pour beaten mixture into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean (about 30 to 35 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oreo torte
directions: Crush Oreos with a rolling pin.
Mix with butter and pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook chocolate, evaporated milk, egg and sugar.
Spread over cookies.
Spoon 1/2 gallon ice cream over mixture.
Spread large container Cool Whip over ice cream. Sprinkle peanuts over Cool Whip.
Store in freezer.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add fried onions on top and bake for another 5 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Heat cream to just below boiling point.
Remove from heat; add honey and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Add fruit pulp when cool. Chill and stir.
Freeze.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Put peppers in blender with 1 cup vinegar and blend.
Pour into 4 or 5-quart pan.
Rinse blender with remaining vinegar; pour into pan and stir in sugar.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Certo and coloring.
Cool and put in jars.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
If too moist, add flour to stiffen.
Roll into ball, then press flat on greased sheets with fork (crisscross).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in bottom of pie shell. (Chop them in small pieces.) Beat eggs, butter, corn syrup and vanilla until well blended. Combine sugar and flour; blend with egg mixture. Pour over nuts in shell. Let stand until nuts rise to surface. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mary's turkey goulash
directions: Cook ground turkey, bell pepper and onion until turkey is brown.
Add garlic, pepper and salt to taste.
Stir in tomato sauce and cook until done.

title: cheesecake(heritage recipe)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 c.cold water in measuring cup. Finish filling cup with boiling water.
pour into food blender. Add all ingredients except powdered milk.
Add it last to avoid packing on blades of blender.
Blend well.

title: orange-onion salad
directions: Layer oranges and onions in dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over onions and oranges.
Marinate for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Then serve.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Add sugar, water, syrup and butter.
Bring to boil then add peanuts.
Bring to boil again and boil for approximately 8 minutes on medium flame.
Take off flame and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Stir until soda is mixed well.
Pour on buttered aluminum foil.
Let cool.
Break up into pieces.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 2 hours and serve.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 4 times.
Add salad dressing, water and vanilla.
Fold in; do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. (You can use any type salad dressing.)

title: baked beef cake
directions: Dice meat.
Make a batter with flour, milk, egg, 1/2 salt and pepper.
Grease baking dish. Put meat in. Sprinkle with balance of salt and pepper.
Pour batter over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve hot. Serves 4.

title: cyndy's cheese broccoli soup
directions: In pot, put vegetables, cover with just enough water and add salt.
Bring to boil, simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not drain. While vegetables are cooking, melt the margarine in a saucepan, whisk in flour.
Add half and half and milk, continue whisking until thick and bubbly.
Stir constantly.

title: cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in 9-in cast-iron skillet.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into hot skillet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve.

title: enchiladas american style
directions: Fry each tortilla in hot oil for 3 seconds.
Drain.
On individual plates, top each tortilla with chili and cheese.
Repeat in layers several times.
Final topping:
Lettuce, tomato, pepper and onion.
Cover with enchilada sauce.
Serves 4.

title: lillian's mustard sauce
directions: Stir the well beaten eggs, sugar, mustard, salt and cayenne. Cook in top of double boiler over medium flame.
Stir constantly until starts to become creamy. When thickens, remove from heat and add the butter and vinegar.

title: a honeyed meal of rice and apples
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; melt butter.
Add apples and honey.
Cook and stir carefully until apples are tender, but still hold their shape, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in hot cooked rice, walnuts and celery.
Sprinkle with orange peel. Makes 6 servings.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Spread chicken on bottom of baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Mix melted butter with Ritz crackers and put on top of chicken and sprinkle poppy seed over the top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato wine
directions: Mix fruits and boiling water.
When cool, add yeast.
Stir every so often for about 10 days, then let stand for at least 2 months before straining.
Use plastic waste can, cover and strain through old (boiled) hose or cheesecloth.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with cooking spray; drain water off spinach.
Add to casserole dish.
Add soup; mix well.
Slice eggs; layer on top.
Add cheese layer on top of eggs.
Crumble bacon and layer on top of eggs.
Mix crumbs and margarine together; cook for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine nuts, dates, soda, and salt in a mixing bowl. Add shortening in boiling water. Allow this mixture to stand 15 minutes. Stir to blend. Beat eggs slightly and add vanilla. Stir in sugar and flour and add to date mixture. DO NOT OVER MIX. Bake in loaf pan at 350 for 1 hour.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Slice about 1/4-inch from top of garlic. Wrap head in foil.
Bake on oven rack 45 minutes or until soft. Cook potatoes 25 minutes.
Drain.
Return potatoes to pot.
Unwrap garlic and squeeze paste over potatoes.
Add milk, salt, butter and pepper.
Mash until blended.

title: samuel's noodle and cheese ala olia
directions: Bring noodles to a boil in a large pot until al dente.
In a large skillet, saute olive oil, garlic, parsley flakes and spices, bringing to a low simmer.
After straining noodles, put them in the skillet of sauce, mixing thoroughly.
Add cheese to each individual serving, stirring to semi-melt.

title: hot hamburger dip
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Combine beef, Velveeta cheese, picante sauce and mushroom soup in a slow cooker.
Cook on High to serving temperature.
Serve on tortilla chips.
Yields 20 servings.

title: old-fashioned banana streusel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a square 9-inch pan with nonfat cooking spray.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt sugar, milk and butter on low heat. Keep it stirred. Cook until soft-ball stage. Take off heat. Add rest of ingredients. Mix well and pour into dish or pan. Let it get cold and cut.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: *Put water in
can
after
emptying contents for use in case a little extra liquid is needed.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown turkey and onion. Add sauces and simmer for 10 minutes. Combine the cottage cheese, eggs and chopped chilies. Have ready the Monterey Jack cheese, Mozzarella cheese and tortillas. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/2 of meat mixture, 4 tortillas, 1/2 of cottage cheese mixture and 1/2 of shredded cheeses; repeat. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Let sit for about 15 minutes before cutting.

title: russian scalloped potatoes
directions: Simmer the onions in half the butter until soft, but not brown.
Add the flour. Cook 5 minutes, then add consomme, sour cream, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Continue cooking 10 minutes over low heat. Slice potatoes thin and saute in remaining butter about 5 minutes. Trim fat from ham and cut ham into strips about 1 x 1/2-inch.
Peel the pickles and slice very thin.
Mix all ingredients with the onion sauce carefully, using a fork.
Place all together in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes. Good with cucumber salad and pumpernickel bread.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend together the tomato sauce, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Reserve 1/2 cup tomato sauce mixture; gently mix the balance with all remaining ingredients. Form into loaf shape and place in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Spread reserved tomato sauce over top of loaf and bake for 1 1/4 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour in pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix well.
Chill.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with 1 1/2-inch cookie cutter.
Dip rounds on both sides in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick with fork.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and put 2 cookies together with filling.

title: cornbread cake appetizer
directions: Bake cornbread in 3 cake pans; cool.
Brown sausage; add chopped onions, pepper, Ro-Tel tomatoes and jalapeno cheese.
Cook until consistency of icing.
Spread on each layer of cornbread. Will look like an iced cake.
Cut in wedges to serve.

title: fried corn
directions: Fry bacon very crisp in skillet.
Remove bacon.
Pour both cans of corn into bacon grease.
Crumble bacon strips and add to corn. Stir at low heat for 5 minutes.
Tastes like fresh corn from the garden.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring potatoes, garlic and water to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook for 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain, reserving 2/3 cup cooking liquid. Mash the potatoes.	Add oil, salt, pepper and reserved liquid; stir until smooth.

title: tortellini primavera
directions: Cook tortellini according to directions on package.
Drain. In large skillet, saute garlic in butter.
Add vegetables.
Saute until crisp-tender.
Add half and half and pepper.
Cook briefly until slightly reduced.
Add tortellini.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Slightly flatten each chicken breast. Place in baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove foil.
Drain.
In saucepan, combine tomatoes, cornstarch and pepper sauce.
Stir to dissolve cornstarch.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Return to oven.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
Garnish with chopped parsley and serve with pasta, if desired.	Serves 4.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Add all ingredients except cabbage and green beans.
Bring to boil, lower heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add cabbage and green beans, bring to boil and simmer until vegetables are tender. Yields 12 servings.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar, eggs and molasses. Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, and ginger. Add dry ingredients to shortening, sugar, egg and molasses mixture. Mix thoroughly. Form into small balls the size of a small walnut. Place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.

title: slow cooker barbecue pot roast
directions: Brown meat in oil in skillet, then transfer to slow cooker. Add peppers, onions and barbecue sauce.
Cover.
Cook on high for 4 to 5 hours or until tender.
Slice and serve with sauce.

title: dan's special banana dessert
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add sugar and pecans.
With heat on medium-high, cook 1 minute.
Add bananas and stir until they are warm.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in brandy and flame.
(If gas stove, carefully tilt pan.
With electric stove, use long stemmed match.)
To serve, pour over pound cake or angel food cake. Serves 2.
Add crushed pineapple for variety.

title: shrimp and grits(delicious)
directions: Cook grits slowly according to directions until only bubble breaks surface now and then, about 40 minutes.
Stir often; add water if needed.
Stir in butter and cheese.
Season to taste with hot pepper sauce, nutmeg and white pepper.
Cover and hold in a warm place, top of double boiler over simmering water.
Saute bacon lightly, until edges are brown, not crisp.

title: curry rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed. Cool.
Chop olives and add to rice. Drain artichoke hearts, saving juice.
Chop and add to rice.

title: cherry cheese dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and oleo.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Combine cream cheese and milk.
Beat until smooth. Add 2 cups sugar.
Beat well.
Fold Cool Whip into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Spread cherry pie filling on top.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix early and let age for at least 24 hours in refrigerator in a covered container.
Serve with carrots, celery sticks, radishes, cauliflower, cucumbers and green pepper.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip together.
Put a layer of graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of pudding mixture on top.
Make another layer of crackers and pour the remaining pudding mixture.
Add another layer of crackers on.
Use chocolate icing for topping.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine and gently
mix all ingredients.
Spread in the bottom of an ungreased
x
12-inch
(2-quart)
baking dish. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until bubbly hot.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup in a 3-quart saucepan until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter; mix in Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let harden.

title: corned beef and cabbage mold
directions: Mix the gelatin and water in saucepan over water at low heat 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in salt, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce.
Gradually stir into mayonnaise in mixing bowl.
Add onion and chill. Stir occasionally until slightly thickened.
Add pickle, celery, cabbage and corned beef.
Mix well. Chill in 6-cup mold.

title: volcano cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, sprinkle nuts, then coconut.
Prepare cake mix according to box directions.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Spoon cake mix over nuts and coconut.
Drop cream cheese mixture by spoonfuls over top of cake mix.
Do not mix cake and topping.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cashew chicken chinese
directions: In a wok, heat peanut oil on high.
Stir-fry vegetables until crisp, placing the veggies that take the longest to cook in the middle of the wok until somewhat crisp.
Then push the veggies out of the middle and up the walls of the wok to make room for the next veggie to go in the middle.
Keep going in this manner until the last veggie has been added.
Broccoli should be steamed and does not take long to cook, so it should be the last veggie you add. Add water to veggies and cover to steam until done.
Add meat and cornstarch to mix.
Stir until thick.
Add cashew nuts.
Serve over rice.

title: raspberry brownies(sacher bites)
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter and chocolate squares over low heat.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing with a wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Spread in greased 15x10x1 inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 15-20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Spread preserves over top of brownies in baking pan.
Cut in half lengthwise and then crosswise to make 4 rectangles.
Loosen edges.
Stack 2 rectangles, preserves side up.
Trim edges if necessary.
Cut into 2x1 inch bars, separate and put on wire racks over waxed paper. Melt chocolate chips and drizzle over each bar.
If chocolate is too stiff, add 1 t. melted shortening to thin.
Chill bars to harden chocolate.
Makes 40.

title: coconut potato cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar, egg and coconut flavoring. Add the biscuit mix and potato flakes.
Chill dough. Roll into small balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes (or until edges turn a little brown).

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cut in margarine.
Add cheese, Rice Krispies and pecans.
Put teaspoon size balls on cookie sheet.
Mash with fork.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: easy dessert
directions: Bake cake according to directions as sheet cake.
Make glaze by heating Pet milk and sugar.
When cake has baked, remove from oven and put holes in the cake immediately.
Pour the glaze over the cake.
When cool, top with Cool Whip.
On top of this, put coconut, as much as you like.
Refrigerate.
It's delicious!

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar.
In cup, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add yeast and all other ingredients to Crisco mixture.
Blend well.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to bake, roll out and cut with biscuit cutter or glass.
Place on baking sheet. Let rise about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Put cabbage in casserole dish.
Sprinkle rice over cabbage and fluff with fork to lightly mix.
Saute hamburger and drain.
Add soup and water; heat for a few minutes.

title: spumoni
directions: Soften ice cream slightly. Layer ice cream, strawberry on bottom, vanilla in the middle and pistachio on top. Sprinkle walnuts between each kind of ice cream.
Can use a 10 x 14 dish or 2 smaller ones.
Sprinkle nuts on top, then decorate with maraschino cherries. cover with plastic wrap or foil and freeze.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine in separate bowl sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning.
Spread bean dip on serving platter, then avocado next.
Next, layer sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle onion, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Serve with scoop Fritos or nacho chips.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Pour sugar over top and let set overnight. Dissolve jello in water.
Add jello and remaining ingredients to cranberries and mix early in the morning.
Serve at lunch.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Stir in brown sugar. Halve pineapple slices.
Place in mixture.
Center with 3 cherry pieces.

title: apple dessert
directions: Slice apples into 8-inch square pan.
Add sugar and cinnamon together.
Mix together with brown sugar, flour, oleo and milk; spread over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are soft, about 45 minutes.
Serve warm with milk or vanilla ice cream.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes
in
enough
water
to
cover until soft; drain. Add other	ingredients
and simmer over low heat about 20 minutes.
Add more or less milk to desired thickness.

title: dwayne's favorite pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple, saving 2 tablespoons of syrup.
Melt butter in 10-inch skillet.
Add brown sugar, stirring until sugar is melted.
Remove from heat. Arrange drained pineapple on sugar mixture in skillet.
Fill centers with cherries and spaces between with nuts.
Set skillet aside.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine melted Crisco, cocoa and salt; then add milk and vanilla.
Mix in sugar in 3 parts.
Mix until smooth and creamy. Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin, if needed for good spreading consistency.
Frost 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers or a 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni. Chip cheese.
Place layer of macaroni, then layer of cheese. Salt each layer of macaroni.
Then add layer of macaroni, then cheese.
Beat egg with sweet milk.
Add butter. Bake at 450° for 1/2 hour. Bake in oblong pan.
Makes large pie.

title: poppy seed piquant
directions: Mix sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Add onion juice and stir slowly.
Add oil, beating constantly, then add poppy seed.
Good on fruit or cabbage slaw.
Keeps real good in refrigerator.

title: finger jello
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix jello and gelatine together.
Pour boiling water in and stir until completely dissolved.
Pour into baking pan.
Set in refrigerator until solid.
Cut into shapes and enjoy!

title: dixie punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Let cool.
Add lemon juice and Dr. Pepper.

title: southern chicken casserole
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
In Dutch oven, fry bacon until crisp. Remove bacon, add chicken browning well on all sides.
Remove to a 2-quart casserole dish as pieces brown.
Cut potatoes lengthwise into 3 slices, add to bacon fat.
Brown on both sides.
Remove and place on top of chicken.
Top potatoes with onions, sprinkle with poultry seasoning, salt, pepper, shallots and parsley.
Top with the bacon.
Cover, bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Slice peaches and place in the bottom of greased pan.
Beat eggs separately.
Sprinkle the rest of ingredients over fruit. Melt shortening and pour over mix.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: macaroni-ham casserole
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Combine sour cream, milk, dry mustard and pepper.
Add to macaroni mixture; mix well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Yields 6 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni
for
15 minutes.
Drain.
Beat eggs well and add
milk.	Put
cooked
macaroni in buttered dish and add eggs and
milk mixture and 1 cup cheese.
Salt.	Mix together. Top with 1/2 cup of cheese.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Add grated cheese to flour, margarine and salt.
Add Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoonful on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: yummy caramel bars
directions: Mix cake mix and 3/4 cup evaporated milk.
Spread 1/2 of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler. Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked layer, then spread melted caramels.
Top with remaining cake batter.
Bake 18 minutes at 350°.
Makes 48 bars.

title: trash bag mix
directions: Melt on low heat in large pan the margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Remove from heat.
Add raisins, peanuts and Rice Chex.
Mix well with wooden spoon.
Put 4x sugar in 8-gallon trash bag.
Pour in mix and shake until all covered.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a casserole. Bake at 350°, or put in crock-pot.
Otherwise, bake for 2 hours.

title: pizzelle
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar gradually.
Add oil and anise; beat until smooth.
Gradually add flour, salt, baking powder and anise seed, if desired.
Drop 3/4 tablespoon of dough on already heated iron.
Will work on either stove type or electric iron.

title: two-tone potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and in two separate bowls, mash white potatoes and sweet potatoes.
Add one tablespoon of butter to each and mix well.
Add egg white and onion powder to the white potatoes.
Add egg yolk and orange peel to the sweet potatoes.

title: peppermint dessert
directions: Crush candy bars. Whip cream; fold in candy.
Chill until serving time.
Top each cake slice with a scoop of ice cream.
Top with whipped cream mixture.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, sprinkle top with a little cinnamon and sugar and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May be served with whipped topping (Cool Whip).

title: chinese cookies
directions: Melt the butterscotch and chocolate chips together in top of a double boiler (until thoroughly melted).
Stir in peanuts and noodles until well covered.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Refrigerate until cool.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in ungreased skillet.
Pour off fat as it accumulates. Mix sausage with rice, soup, onion and celery. Place in 2-quart casserole.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine all the items by hand.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan until cake springs back at touch.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper all together for 10 minutes; set aside for 5 minutes.
Add Certo and food coloring if desired.
Pour in hot jars and seal.
Really good with dressing and meats; hot.

title: krispie chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix.
Add chocolate chips, Cocoa Krispies and nuts.
Mix together.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and press lightly with back of spoon.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: granny's pig pickin' cake(two layer cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake approximately 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: dandelion greens
directions: In a large pan, place dandelion greens, salt and water.
Cook about 10 to 20 minutes or until greens are tender.
Drain well.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage, meat bits and onions in a bowl.
Place noodles, seed and almonds in a plastic bag.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and seasoning in a jar and shake very well.
Just before serving, mix the 3 together and enjoy!

title: gourmet meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chili sauce.
Shape in a loaf in a shallow baking dish.
Score loaf with wooden spoon and fill score marks with chili sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican breakfast
directions: Whisk together the first 7 ingredients for sauce.
Cook butter, eggs, cottage cheese and parsley.
Add 1 cup sausage to sausage and mix.
Put a little sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll egg and sausage mixture in flour tortillas.
Place in pans.
Cover with rest of sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: Boil sugar in water for 3 minutes.
Add jello and dissolve. Add juices and stir well.
Pour into milk cartons and freeze. Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.
When ready to serve, add 1 quart of ginger ale to 1/2 gallon of punch.
Mix to slush.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese. Mix well by hand and form into ball. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine meat, eggs, milk, bread crumbs and mustard.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread brown sugar in bottom of pan.
Pack mixture firmly on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese delight
directions: Grate cheese.
Make a paste of butter, seasonings and cheese. Spread thickly on bread and place a slice of bacon on top of each piece.
Place in large pan and put under broiler until bacon is brown or bake in moderate oven (375°) for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together in a large mixing bowl (set aside).
In saucepan put 1 stick margarine, 1/2 cup shortening, 3 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup water.
Bring to a rapid boil and pour at once over flour and sugar, mix, stir well.
Add 2 eggs to mixture and mix well.
Add 1 teaspoon soda to 1/2 cup buttermilk or sour milk, 1 tsp vanilla and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a 16 X 11 or 12 X 18 inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: janet's party punch
directions: Mix orange juice, lemon juice and grenadine syrup.
Pour over a block of ice to chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale or 7-Up.
Garnish with fruit.
This is a great thirst quencher.
Plan on a double batch.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Beat with fork slightly. Add remaining ingredients except cereal and margarine.
Pour into shallow 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Combine cereal and margarine and sprinkle on top.
(It will puff up.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: joe bob's pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in crust.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.
You can use lime
lemonade and green food coloring.

title: christmas breakfast
directions: Cut bread into pieces; mix with cheese.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Stir in salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour this over bread and cheese.
Mix fried bacon pieces or ham through and sprinkle some on top (I use more bacon and ham for top).
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Serve at once.

title: ham roll appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese for 20 to 30 seconds in microwave.
Slice ham into 1/4-inch long pieces.
Cut greens from scallions just short of the length of the ham slices.
Spread cream cheese over the ham slices; take 1 cut slice from onions and place onto ham with cream cheese.
Roll so it looks like a pinwheel and secure with a toothpick.
Drain olives and cube the Cheddar cheese and pepperoni to a little smaller than an olive.
Place 1 ham pinwheel, 1 black olive or 1 green olive, 1 cheese cube and 1 pepperoni on a toothpick.
Serve on a large platter.

title: german fudge cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place butter and chocolate bar in microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 minute; stir and microwave 1 minute more, if needed.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine eggs, flour, sugar and salt; mix lightly.
Stir in chocolate mixture, vanilla and pecans.
Pour batter into muffin cups and bake about 30 minutes, or until cupcakes test done. Makes 24.

title: rosemary yams
directions: Peel and cut yams into large chunks.
Bruise garlic by mashing with side of chef knife.
Place all ingredients in covered casserole dish.
Bake or microwave until tender, stirring at intervals to baste with herbs and oil.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and smooth over top and sides of cauliflower.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes and serve.

title: shrimp, avocado and grapefruit salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl; stir in peeled and deveined shrimp.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight. Drain shrimp; reserving marinade sauce to be use as salad dressing.

Make individual salads by placing large leaf on salad plate; cut remaining lettuce in strips and place on top of leaf. Arrange shrimp in center; alternate slices of avocados and pink grapefruit around shrimp.
Used reserved marinade sauce as dressing.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased bundt pan. Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: chicken packets(makes 8)
directions: Mix chicken, cream cheese, milk, chives, salt and pepper. (This can then be frozen.)

title: johnna's breakfast cheese
directions: In a heavy skillet, melt butter.
Stir in sugar and add cheese that has been cut in small pieces.
Let come to a slow boil and cook for 3 to 5 minutes on low.
Stir often so it won't scorch. Spread on toast or biscuits.
Also good for an after school snack.

title: western beans
directions: Cook ground beef.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: porkie pine meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup and milk.
Shape into balls and place in a casserole.
Combine soup and milk; mix well.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and cook at 350° about 1 hour.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight. Excellent with crackers or chips.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: You will need paper baking cups.

title: aunt pauline's "lemonade stretcher"
directions: Mix sugar and lemon juice.
Stir until sugar has dissolved. Add cold water and grape juice.
Add thin slice of lemon peel to each glass of lemonade.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup (no water), sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Crush corn flakes and stir in remaining butter. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Cook rice
according to directions on the box.	Fry the bacon. Drain
