Cut into strips. Add green pepper, onion, bacon and eggs to rice.
Season with soy sauce before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: "lite" broccoli soup
directions: Simmer vegetables until tender in chicken broth.
In medium bowl, combine milk, cornstarch, salt, pepper and thyme.
Add milk mixture to vegetables; cook until soup is slightly thick, stirring constantly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Add oil and water. Cook 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from pan.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers or toast rounds.

title: parmesan twists
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In a 9-inch pie pan, combine Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
Divide bread dough into 8 sections; divide each section into 4 pieces (total of 32 pieces of dough). Roll each piece into a 4-inch rope.
Dip each rope in butter; roll in Parmesan mixture.
Twist rope 3 times.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: In deep, cast iron skillet, add oil and flour; make a very light roux. Add onions, celery and bell pepper. Smother for about 10 or 15 minutes. Add shelled crawfish and fat. Add seasoning to taste. Cover tightly and let simmer, stirring constantly. Add about 1/2 cup water; cook about 15 or 20 minutes. Add onion tops and parsley.

title: quick chicken curry
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a light boil in a saucepan.
Turn to low and let simmer (stirring occasionally) for 30 minutes.
Serve over hot rice with a variety of toppings such as peanuts, coconut, raisins, mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Be as creative and brave as you like.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butter; add chocolate chips and marshmallows until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in oats and coconut.
Put on waxed paper in teaspoon heaps.

title: basic three bean salad
directions: Choose an attractive color combination for the beans. Combine beans in large bowl with onion, then toss with mixed dressing.

title: kim's quiche
directions: Saute onion in margarine; mix in spinach, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
In bowl, mix all wet ingredients and Parmesan cheese. Add sauteed onion mixture.
Pour into pie shell (deep dish).
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Good on fruit salad especially with mandarin oranges and lettuce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add dry ingredients; mix well. Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. It freezes real nice.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; shape into 1-inch round meat balls. Fry meat balls in butter or oleo on all sides.
Remove to casserole dish.
To pan drippings add soup and remaining sour cream.
Heat until smooth and pour over meat balls.

title: double decker blueberry pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice in a bowl.
Mix gelatin and water in sauce pan and bring to a boil.
Cool slightly and add to milk mixture.
Add 1 1/4 cup blueberries to this mixture.
Fold in 1 cup sour cream.
Pour into crust.
Spread 1 1/4 cup blueberries over the top.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or over night.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon strips.
Pour into pan. Place bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, along with raisins; bring to a boil. Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.
Makes 1 pie.

title: sangria
directions: Mix small amount of wine, lemon peel, orange slice and sugar in a pitcher that will hold one bottle of wine.
Mix ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Add the remaining one-half bottle of wine; stir.
Add 12 ice cubes and fill pitcher with soda water. Stir to mix and serve.

title: baked fish and gravy(catfish or trout)
directions: Mix. Pour over fish in pan.
Let simmer about 15 minutes.
For more gravy, double recipe.
Serve over cooked rice.
Very good.

title: crunchy coated potatoes(microwave)
directions: Place oleo in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Microwave on Full power for 30 to 45 seconds or until melted.
Combine cornflakes, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, minced onion and salt in small bowl.
Coat potatoes with butter and roll in crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish and cover with paper towel.
Microwave on Full power for 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are just tender. Allow to stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt together candy bars and 1/2 cup butter.
Cream remaining butter and sugar; add eggs, flour and buttermilk; stir.
Add melted candy mix.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350°
for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
except
pastry
shell, in a saucepan;
cook
over medium heat until butter melts, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into prepared pastry shell.
Bake at 400°
for
minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes or until set.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Cream Ricotta and cream cheese.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Add flour and cornstarch gradually.
Add melted butter and sour cream.
Fold in whipped cream.
Grease sides and bottom of 10 x 3-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and let stand in oven for 1 hour longer.
Do not open to peek at any time!!!

title: tuna fritters
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients and add the tuna, onion, green pepper and parsley.
Mix well.
Drop from spoon into deep fat until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend sugar, bananas, margarine and eggs for 2 minutes.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nuts (optional).
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In an electric mixer, mix first three ingredients on low to mix completely.
Add and mix the sugar, salt, egg and vanilla.	(Mix vanilla and egg together before adding to sugar and salt.)	Add 2 cups flour and mix on medium for 2 minutes.
Add 2 cups flour and mix well (will look like batter).

title: triple chocolate mess
directions: Spray your crockpot with non-stick spray.
Mix all ingredients well.
Cook on low for 6-8 hours.
Try not to lift the lid.
Serve with ice cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare ground beef (drain).
Add taco seasoning mix.
Set aside.
Prepare lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and onions.
Mix all together carefully.
Combine with chips and mix well with Catalina dressing.

title: 10 minute meatballs
directions: Shape combined mixture well into small patties.
Drop patties into hot condensed tomato soup to which 1/2 cup of water has been added.

title: salmon with asparagus sauce
directions: In skillet, heat oil.
Add garlic; saute.
In blender, add asparagus, garlic, salt and pepper; process until smooth.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise and mustard; spread on fillet.
Transfer to an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan (nonstick).
Add wine and bake fish until flaky, about 15 minutes.
Remove pan from oven.
Turn over and broil.
Spread asparagus puree over fish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil just until heated.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard, honey and tarragon.
Place chicken breasts on grill or rack of broiler pan; brush with half of salad dressing mixture.
Grill or broil for 8 minutes.
Turn; brush with remaining salad dressing mixture.
Continue grilling or broiling 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jack's spicy peanut sauce
directions: Add hot water to peanut butter and stir until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients and whisk together.
Heat, but do not boil. Pour over broccoli, tofu, brown rice and/or any other vegetable combination of your choice.

title: rum cake
directions: Put pecans in bottom of well-greased (use Pam) Bundt pan.
Mix all other ingredients for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Mix together the tuna, soups, milk and peas.
Add noodles; mix well.
Pour into nonstick sprayed 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 10.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape into patties and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover pan with foil.
Brown patties in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Drain grease from pan; mix soups together.
Pour over patties; cover with foil.
Return to oven for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: glop
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain.
Combine meat, can of tomato soup and green beans in casserole dish.
Top with the cooked mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: grandma's ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well. Stir in molasses. Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Roll dough into balls about the size of walnuts. Dip tops in granulated sugar.
Place 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Thumbprint and fill with jam.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown beef in large pot; drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for approximately two hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: macaroni seafood salad
directions: Prepare dinner mix according to package directions, except omit butter.
Stir in mayonnaise, cucumber dressing and onion. Fold in shrimp and tomato.
Cover; chill in freezer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Peel, seed and chop avocado.
Fold into macaroni mixture.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl if desired.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: easy chicken in gravy
directions: Place chicken in baking pan with other ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice or noodles and favorite vegetable.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip, sour cream and vanilla.
Make layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: dirty rice
directions: Place all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 425° for 45 minutes.
Cover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: sweet potato pudding(microwave)
directions: Cook the potatoes on Full power for 15 to 17 minutes. Combine all ingredients, blending well.
Pour into an 8 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish.
Spread topping over surface.
Cook on 8th level of power for 8 to 10 minutes or until set. Topping will harden into a crust as dish cools slightly.

title: doug hale's famous beef jerky
directions: Combine all ingredients (except meat) in a large bowl.
Mix very well.
Add the sliced beef and soak for 30 to 45 minutes. Take out of mixture and put in a dehydrator for approximately 18 hours, rotating trays every three hours.

title: guacamole superior - mexico
directions: Peel avocados and mash them coarse.
Add all of the remaining ingredients and stir until combined.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw broccoli (if frozen). Mix rice and broccoli together.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix and pour into a baking dish, cover and bake for 30 minutes. Uncover and finish baking for 30 minutes.

title: peanutty popcorn balls
directions: In a large bowl mix popcorn and peanuts; set aside.
On a preheated grill combine sugar and corn syrup.
Cook and stir until brown sugar dissolves and mixture boils for about 3 minutes. Place peanut butter and vanilla in a small bowl.
Quickly stir in hot syrup mixture.
Pour over popcorn mixture at once.
Stir to coat as well.
With buttered hands; form into balls.
Makes about 6 popcorn balls.

title: blueberry betty
directions: Cook blueberries, sugar, salt and lemon juice for 10 minutes. Pour into a shallow baking dish.
Arrange slices of French toast on top.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook peeled and diced eggplant in boiling salted water for 15 minutes.
Drain well.
Beat eggs until fluffy, add milk and then soak bread in broken pieces in milk and egg mixture.
Add onions, cheese, mushrooms, salt and pepper (to taste).
Mix well.
Add drained eggplant to this mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Blend cake mix and butter together. Add chopped nuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: constitution cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and white sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, vanilla, beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes or until cookies are golden brown.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: mom's excellent shrimp louisianne
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy skillet; saute vegetables.
Add raw peeled shrimp and saute a few minutes longer.
Stir in flour, salt and chili powder.
Add milk gradually and cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Add ketchup and parsley.
Add optional items if you want. Cook, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed adding 5 Tbsp. creme de menthe. Bake
9 x 13 pan.
Cool.
Spread fudge topping over cake (warm fudge topping slightly to make it more spreadable).
Add 5 Tbsp. creme de menthe to Cool Whip.
Spread over fudge sauce. Refrigerate.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: spanish rice
directions: Rinse rice and let soak about 5 minutes.
Drain rice and brown in bacon grease.
Add 1 can tomato sauce.
Add 2 cans water and onion.

title: coconut party cake
directions: While cake is baking, in 9 x 13-inch pan, mix together the Eagle Brand milk and creme de cacao.
When cake is done, and while hot, punch full of holes with fork and pour mixture slowly over cake.
Cover.
Let set a few hours or overnight in refrigerator. Mix Cool Whip and coconut together.
Spread over top of cake. Sprinkle with ground pecans.

title: toffee bar crunch pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add instant pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fold in whipped topping and chopped toffee.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer and let stand 10 minutes to soften before serving. Store leftovers in freezer.

title: creole catsup
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cover and simmer over medium heat until onions are soft.
Remove from heat and mash with a potato masher.
Force the mixture through a sieve until only seeds and skins are left.
This may be diluted with vinegar if it is too thick or too strong.
Pour into cans and seal according to directions.

title: dirt cake
directions: Buy an 8-inch plastic flower pot and a trowel.

title: quick and easy strawberry creme puffs
directions: Chill creme puffs in refrigerator.
Slice creme puffs according to already established groves.
Lay flat on serving tray.
Top with sliced strawberries.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve.
Looks very pretty served on a round tray with a paper lace doily.
(If you're a chocolate lover like me, you can drizzle melted chocolate over the top.)

title: southern pralines
directions: Mix all together except vanilla.
Cook at 230° or to a soft ball.
Stir often while cooking.
Remove from stove and add vanilla.
Beat and beat.
Drop on wax paper.

title: chocolate sundae cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, cocoa and water. Mix well. Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan. Place marshmallows evenly on top. Make cake batter following package directions. Pour into pan. Top with nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: date and nut pinwheels
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar together.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, salt and baking soda. Make into 2 balls.
Roll on wax paper.
Add 1/2 of filling (recipe to follow) to each and roll up. Freeze and slice to bake at 350° for 7-10 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Presoak beans overnight.
Chop the following in a food processor:
onion, garlic, bell pepper and celery.
Cook the beans and ham bone together.
(I buy my bone at a honey baked ham store.)

When you start cooking the beans, add the onion, bell pepper, garlic, celery, salt, pepper, oregano, basil, crab boil, Tabasco, Worcestershire, bay leaves, tomato sauce and parsley. Bring to a boil; turn down and cook for 2 to 3 hours until beans are soft.
Taste for salt and pepper.
Take out a cup of beans; mash them and put them back in.
Cut sausage in 1-inch pieces; add to beans the last 45 minutes of cooking time.
Serve over rice. This is great served with corn muffins.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Butter foil.
Cover with saltine crackers side by side, close together.
Boil together butter and sugar 4 minutes.
Pour over saltines.
Bake at 350° for 14 minutes. Immediately cover with milk chocolate chips which will melt. Spread as they melt.
Refrigerate to cool.
Break apart after cooling.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan; cut rolls in fours and roll the pieces in a mixture of white sugar and cinnamon.
Drop the pieces in a Bundt pan (even) until all pieces are used.
Melt the butter or oleo with the brown sugar and pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or glass casserole dish with Pam.
Mix first 9 ingredients until blended into one color.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle top with cake mix.
Drizzle margarine over top and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: spiced pineapple pickups
directions: Drain syrup of pineapple into medium saucepan.
Add sugar, vinegar, cloves, cinnamon stick and salt; cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks; heat to boiling. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Drain and serve with cocktail picks.

title: gobs (sandwich cookies)
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order given, except for powdered sugar.
Mix 2 minutes on medium speed.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until center springs back when touched.
Cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pineapple and cherry in. Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Melt 2 sticks butter and drizzle on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes with sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt and Crisco together.
Pour boiling water over mixture; let cool.
Add beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast in boiling water.
Add to mixture.
Add flour.
Put in refrigerator in a glass or metal bowl for at least 4 hours.
Roll and cut out rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Layer bananas, pudding and cookies.
After every two layers top with whipped cream. Chill.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, peas, onion, mayo, sugar, salt and pepper.
Top with cheese.
Mix Ritz crackers and butter and top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry sauce salad
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and 1 can of cranberry sauce and refrigerate until it begins to set up.
Stir in sour cream, celery and nuts.
Return to refrigerator until it sets up.

title: chicken cordon bleu shortcut
directions: In medium skillet over medium-high heat, heat margarine.
Add Chicken and cook 10 minutes or until browned.
Set chicken aside.

stirring

Cut	in squares.
Serve on lettuce leaf with mayonnaise
and
a cherry half.

title: sausage cheese spread
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage together; drain.
Cut cheese into squares and melt with beef and sausage.
Serve hot over Triscuit crackers.

title: peanut butter cup
directions: Butter pan.
Mix the first five ingredients; pat mixture in bottom of pan.
Melt chocolate chips and 1/2 stick of butter. Pour over top of peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: dumplings
directions: Put flour and salt together.
Add egg.
Put margarine into boiling water.
Mix and roll out.
This may be cooked now or frozen in strips to use as needed.

title: halloween haystacks
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour while hot over cereal.
Toss to coat.
Use 2 spoons and quickly put in mounds on wax paper.

title: chocolate peanut butter apples
directions: You will need 6 to 8 wooden skewers.
Wash and dry apples thoroughly.
Insert a wooden skewer into each apple.
Set aside. Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter chips with oil in top of double boiler or a heavy 1 1/2 quart saucepan over low heat; stir constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat; dip apples in mixture, tilting pan as needed.
Twirl to remove excess coating; place apples on waxed-papered cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm. Makes 6 to 8.

title: candied carrots (high) - microwave
directions: Scrape carrots and cut into thin strips.
Place in a deep 1 1/2-quart casserole; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Heat 1 minute; spoon sauce over carrots.
Cover and microwave 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir and baste with sauce.
Microwave an additional 3 1/2 minutes.
Heat, uncovered, 3 minutes.

title: glazed sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water to cover for 20 to 25 minutes or until fork-tender.
Let cool to touch; peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange slices in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Combine brown sugar and next 7 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly and thickened.
Pour over sweet potatoes; sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and bananas.
Mix in dry ingredients and stir in nuts.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: sweet potato bonbons
directions: Mash sweet potatoes until light and fluffy.
Beat in butter, sugar, salt and orange rind.
Let cool.
Divide into 12 portions. Press potatoes around each marshmallow half, being careful to keep marshmallow in center.
Shape into ovals.
Coat each with melted butter.
Roll in crushed corn flakes.
top with pecan half and place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in very hot oven at 450° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, grapes, celery, onions, orange segments and water chestnuts in large bowl.
Mix yogurt and soy sauce.
Pour over chicken mixture; toss.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours until chilled.
Serve on salad greens.
Yields 6 servings.

title: clam chowder
directions: All all ingredients except clams in a 6-quart pot.
Cook vegetables until tender.
Add clams and juice last.
Simmer 15 minutes, then serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add taco seasoning to browned ground beef with 1 cup of water.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups boiling water; add cranberry sauce. Drain pineapple and add to mixture.
Add chopped nuts; mix well. Pour 1/2 into bowl and refrigerate.

title: ruthie's cherry fruit salad
directions: Dump in bowl; stir, chill and serve.

title: sausage and lentil stew
directions: Cut sausage into 1/4-inch slices, cut each slice in half. Place in skillet with Pam and saute 3 minutes.
Add leek and garlic and cook 3 minutes.
Put lentils, broth, sausage, leeks and garlic in large pan and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in thyme and remaining ingredients and cook until lentils are tender.

title: striped delight
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat the cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth. Fold in half the Cool Whip. Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding as directed on package, using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours or overnight. Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding. Garnish with grated chocolate.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch, sugar and nutmeg and salt.
Add butter with a fork or blender until crumbly.
Spread in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Pour the half and half over or enough to almost fill the shell.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.

Remove from oven. Break the filling; crush gently with a rubber or plastic spatula, being careful not to puncture the bottom of pastry underneath. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until filling bubbles up thick and is a light brown, about 45 minutes.

title: trifle
directions: Beat together 1 1/2 cups water and condensed milk.
Add pudding.
Beat and chill for 5 minutes.
Beat cream until thick. Add to chilled pudding mixture.
Drain peaches.
Cut cake in half. Slice first half in small slices.
Place on bottom of dish. Sprinkle with orange juice.
Put 1/2 of the peaches on cake.
Put 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Repeat again cake, peaches and pudding. Top with chopped nuts or sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix eggs, milk, flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Pour cooking oil in deep fryer until about 2 inches deep.
Heat until oil is hot.
Pour mixture through funnel into oil, moving it in a circular motion, then crisscross until you make a cake about the size of a large doughnut.
Brown it, turn over, remove from fryer and drain.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and/or cinnamon.

title: plum cake
directions: Spray angel food cake pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 50
minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp and noodles (by directions).
Drain and put into a large bowl.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Serves approximately 6.

title: homestyle chicken and sausage
directions: In large open roasting pan, mix potatoes, sausage and salad oil.
Bake 15 minutes.
Add chicken pieces and next five ingredients; toss to mix with ingredients in pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Separate green beans under warm running water.
Drain. Sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until chicken and vegetables are tender.

title: sharon's punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Sherbet should be in small chunks and strawberries could be sliced if desired.
Serves 20 people.

title: juanita's pistachio nut salad
directions: Mix together pudding and Cool Whip.
When completely dissolved, add the rest of the ingredients.
Chill for minimum of 1 hour and serve cold.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix these items and add to oatmeal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dish pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a LARGE bowl, cream sugar, brown sugar, vanilla, oil and eggs together. Add flour, baking soda, salt and oats. Mix well. Stir in cereal, coconut, nuts and chips. (May have to use your hands to mix thoroughly.) Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Move to wire rack to cool. Makes 10 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Brown beef in small roaster.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Let mixture sit in the refrigerator for several hours, covered.
It will turn into a deep yellow color.
Place in a bowl on a tray with the vegetables stacked around it.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to batter alternately with buttermilk; stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten whites.
Pour into three greased and floured pans or long sheet pan; makes large cake.
Bake at 350° until done; cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: delicious pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening until resembles corn meal. Combine water, vinegar and egg. Add a little at a time to flour to form soft dough. Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Roll out pastry and trim.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix
sugar,
spices,
eggs
and
melted margarine.
Add mashed potatoes.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cut together flour, sugar and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Beat together remaining ingredients.
Pour over first part after cooked.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: soy sauce marinade
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Use as a marinade for meats and vegetables.

title: lentil nut loaf
directions: Cook the lentils in 3 pints of water for 1 hour.
Saute onions, garlic and celery in a little oil until tender.
Mix with lentils.
Add seasonings and other ingredients.
Mix well and put into 2 oiled loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or more.
Serve plain or with tomato sauce or hot sauce.
Serving Size:
16. Preparation Time:

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream cheese, margarine and vanilla.
Add powdered sugar.

title: chicken breast
directions: Place a small amount (1 to 2 tablespoons) olive oil in a frying pan.
Wash and pat chicken breast dry.
Place in hot oil and brown on both sides.
Slice onion and slice fresh mushrooms over chicken. Lower heat and cover until done, 15 to 20 minutes.
Very good over rice.
Low-fat, but oh! so good!!

title: johnny mazetti
directions: Brown beef, peppers, celery and onion. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook noodles and drain; set aside. Add to meat mixture the tomato soup, sauce and paste. Add mushrooms and olives last. Mix noodles and meat mixture in a casserole dish; top with grated cheese. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Last 15 minutes of cooking, remove cover.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a bowl.
Combine beaten egg, applesauce, shortening and flavoring together.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Nuts may be added, if desired.
Bake in 1 large bread pan for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Place 1/12 of mixture on each tortilla.
Roll and place seam side down in a greased baking dish.

title: chopped italian salad
directions: Toss to combine all of the above ingredients.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak.
Add onion, salt, pepper, mushrooms and soup. Simmer until meat is done.
Just before serving, add sour cream. Serve over noodles or wild rice.

title: broccoli and ham casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender (crisp).

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O; pour in glass dish and let set.
Mix lemon Jell-O, softened cream cheese and marshmallows; pour over strawberry Jell-O and let jell.
Mix lime Jell-O and pour over lemon Jell-O; let set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: a la king quiche
directions: In bowl combine soup, eggs and cream.
Toss flour with remaining ingredients except pie shell.
Pour mixture over vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Brown pork loin chops or pork chops in small amount of oil or cooking spray.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook rice in water with green pepper, onion, celery, margarine and salt.
Bring to a boil; turn heat down very low and cover with a lid.
Simmer for an additional 12 to 14 minutes.
Rice should be almost, but not quite done.
Add chili sauce and warm with rice mixture, stirring constantly.
Place in baking pan or dish.
If not moist enough, add a small amount of water (like 1/4 cup).
Cover with browned pork chops or pork loin chops.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until chops are done.
(Rice will finish cooking while baking and moisture will be absorbed.)

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Add eggs, nuts, oil, pineapple, vanilla and bananas. Stir.
Do not beat until mixed well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
(I use rectangular cake pan.) Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Freeze until almost time to use. Thaw and add chilled ginger ale.

title: ham potato soup
directions: Wash and peel potatoes and quarter them.
Put in pan of water and boil with one chopped onion.
When potatoes are done, add the condensed milk and chopped ham.
Let it cook on medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes or until ham is warm.
Add enough instant potatoes to make it creamy.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crusts according to package directions, for 2 crust 9-inch pie.
In large bowl, combine all filling ingredients; toss lightly.
Spoon apple mixture into pie-crust lined pans.
Top with second crust and flute; cut slits in several places.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender and crust is golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold together in order all of the ingredients. Refrigerate if possible overnight.

title: old time popcorn balls
directions: Cook ingredients until soft ball stage.
Add 1 pinch of cream of tartar or 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
You may add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir several times. When done, break into small pieces.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine the sugar, milk and marshmallows.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring until the sugar dissolves and marshmallows melt.
Remove from the heat. Stir in peanut butter.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square baking pan.
Cool.
When firm, cut into squares. Yields 3 dozen pieces. If cooking for two: Fudge will keep for several weeks wrapped or stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: cherry delight
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Mix in a large bowl the pineapple, Cool Whip and evaporated milk.
Add the cherry pie filling.
Mix well and refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Serve. Needs to be refrigerated when not serving it.

title: salmon patties
directions: Remove bones and black skin from salmon; flake.
Add onion, egg and 3/4 cup cracker crumbs.
Mix with clean hands and make into patties.
Dip patties into remaining cracker crumbs.
Fry in vegetable oil until golden brown.
Bring to a boil the cornstarch, lemon juice, water, salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir so lumping will not occur.
Dip over salmon patties and serve.

title: carrot pineapple muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside. Mix sugar, oil, eggs, carrots, pineapple and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to wet.
Stir until moistened.
Spoon into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel rice krispies bars
directions: Melt caramels with water in saucepan over low heat.
Stir frequently until smooth.
Pour over cereal and nuts; toss until well coated.
With greased fingers, press mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt and mix chocolate and butterscotch morsels together.
Spread over cereal in pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: snappy cocktail meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine brown gravy mix with ground beef, parsley flakes and the horseradish.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs and put on shallow baking pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a baking dish.
Place a slice of Swiss cheese on each piece of chicken.
Stir together the soup and water.
Spread evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken in casserole
directions: Arrange all ingredients in casserole and cook for about 2 hours in slow oven (325°).
Serves 4.

title: chicken-andouille gumbo
directions: Boil chicken to reduce grease.
Remove the skin and debone if you desire.
I do this.

title: polish sausage casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Pour all ingredients in skillet with liquid.
Top with cheese.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
I use turkey Polish sausage.
Tastes great and is not greasy.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Add soup and vegetables.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Add sugars, syrup, cream, cream of tartar and salt.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from fire and beat 2 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Beat again 10 minutes; add pecans and drop on wax paper. If it gets too hard, add a little hot water.

title: snappy tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Cover and chill at least 30 minutes to allow flavors to blend.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Fill 2 loaf pans (greased and floured) half full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: our favorite pie crust(from pioneer cookbook)
directions: Use a pastry blender to cut shortening into dry ingredients. Combine egg yolk, vinegar and ice water and stir until smooth. Add to dry ingredients by sprinkling one tablespoon at a time and tossing dough with a fork until water is absorbed.
When all water is absorbed, mold into two balls for a top and bottom crust.

title: savory pepper steak
directions: Cut steaks into strips.
Combine 1/4 cup flour, salt and pepper; toss with steak strips to coat thoroughly.
Add to crock-pot with onion, garlic and half of green pepper strips; stir.
Combine tomatoes with beef base, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into crock-pot, moistening meat well. Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 12 hours.

title: custard pie
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Gradually pour over slightly beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer in dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour, covered with foil.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar, chiles and spices.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Dip each tortilla in warm grease to soften.
Put 2 tablespoons cheese and chicken, rolled up in tortilla; place seam side down in pan.
Blend sour cream into sauce and pour over tortillas.
Put rest of cheese on top.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Blend in salt and flour.
Return to heat, add milk stirring constantly until sauce thickens a little and is smooth.
Add cheese to hot macaroni.
Spread in buttered 13x9 inch pan.
Pour sauce over macaroni.
Bake at 375 degrees about 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with green beans and applesauce.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with oleo.
Save 1 cup stuffing for top.
Mix rest of stuffing with all other ingredients.
Put in greased (oleo) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Heat chilies and butter together in top of double boiler until cheese is completely melted.
Add chopped onion and stir until onion is soft.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to cheese mixture.
Serve in chafing dish with large corn chips or Tostitos.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tortillas and cheese. Dip both sides of tortilla in mixture, then fill with mixture, roll and place in baking dish.
Top with cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: biscuits on creamy chicken
directions: Heat soup, sour cream, milk, chicken, salt and pepper just to boiling.
Add peas.
Reduce heat and keep warm while preparing biscuits.
Pour chicken mixture into ungreased 7 X 11-inch oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Drop biscuits on top of mixture (8-10 biscuits).
Bake at 425 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Scald chicken and beef bones.
Cover with water.
Cover pot and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and simmer 1 hour.
Remove fat and add salt and pepper.
Depending on what manner chicken is served, parts may be removed when tender, before falling apart.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Pour in casserole dish and top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until browned.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Soften leaves by dipping a few at a time in boiling water. One leaf at a time, lay it down with the rough side up and plac a teaspoon of stuffing in the center.
Fold bottom of leaf over the stuffing, then fold it from each side to the middle.
Roll tightly, forming a roll about 3 to 4 inches long and 1/2 to 1 inch long.
Pack rolls, open ends down, in tight rows and layer on a steamer rack in saucepan.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and lemon juice.
Crush garlic.
Mix with remaining lemon juice and pour over the last layer or rolls.
Simmer in steamer for about 1 1/2 hours or until leaves and stuffing are tender.

title: breakfast hot dish
directions: Place croutons in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Top with cheese.
Cook sausage in skillet until brown; drain on paper towels.
Place sausage over cheese.
Beat eggs; mix with mustard, milk, mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Pour over sausage.
May be refrigerated overnight.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: bran muffins
directions: Put bran cereal in large bowl.
Add boiling water.
Cream sugar and oil; add egg whites, buttermilk and bran cereal.
Stir together dry ingredients and fold into all cereal mixture until moistened.
Add raisins.
Spray muffin tins with Pam.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes. Remove to rack to finish cooling.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat 4 egg yolks, condensed milk and Key lime juice until thick. Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Fry bacon; remove and drain, leaving fat in pan.
Saute onion and garlic in bacon fat.
Mix in bacon. Combine cheese, eggs, sour cream, nutmeg and
salt and pepper to taste.
Spread half of the bacon-onion mixture in the bottom of the pie shell.
Pour in cheese mixture and add remaining bacon mixture.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake pie 30 to 35 minutes, until a knife inserted into the custard comes out clean.
Set aside for several hours and reheat at 350° for about 20 minutes before serving.

title: prune cake
directions: Can use 1 3/4 cups prunes and no raisins, if preferred.

title: bierok
directions: Thaw and pat into 6-inch rounds.
Put filling on.
Place second round on top and pinch edges down.
Bake at 375°.
Butter top after baking.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.

title: pumpkin crunch cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour into a waxed paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 box yellow cake mix on top; then sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts.
Pour 1 cup melted butter over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
When cool, flip over onto a platter and peel off waxed paper.

title: mexican layered casserole
directions: Brown
ground
beef; add seasoning mix and 1 cup water. Simmer until
most
of the water is absorbed.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole layer beef mixture, beans and shredded cheese.
Heat in
350° oven
until
cheese
is
melted
(about 20 minutes). Remove
from oven
and top with sour cream, tomatoes and lettuce.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: green chili(slow cooker)
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add everything to slow cooker. Cook on low heat 6 to 8 hours.
If you make it on the stove, bring to a boil and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours. To thicken, add dry bread crumbs until desired thickness.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa; add milk and melted butter, vanilla and beat well.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 11-inch baking pan.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Place fish in greased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Make white sauce from butter, flour, dry mustard, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour sauce over fillets.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together and top with almonds and Rice Krispies.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream custard
directions: Gather tender leaves and blossoms when full grown.
Dry at room temperature.
When dry, rub into small particles.
Seal in jars.
This will help it to retain flavor.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, butter and egg in a large bowl. Stir in flour.
Press bottom and 1/2 inch up side of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake until edges are light brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Combine water and jello.
Partially set jello.
Fold in other ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine potatoes, ham and onion in a greased 1-quart casserole; set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat; stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add cheese, salt and pepper; stir until cheese melts.
Pour over potato mixture and stir gently to mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Garnish with parsley. Yield:
2 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs and add all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in 4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and roll each piece in it and place in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Melt butter and mix with brown sugar.
Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deeanna's sausage upside-down cornbread
directions: Cook sausage, onion and green pepper in skillet until sausage is brown and crumbly.
Stir in flour.
Add tomato paste, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Cut Cheddar into 1/2-inch cubes and add to skillet.
Spread evenly into 9-inch square pan.
Prepare muffin mix according to package directions; spread over sausage.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30-35 minutes.
Let stand approximately 5 minutes; loosen edges with knife; invert onto serving dish and serve immediately.

title: six in one cookies
directions: Dough:
Cream butter; gradually add sugars.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.

title: mommy's nut loaf
directions: Mix together. Pour into well-greased pan. Bake 1/2 hour.

title: old fashioned deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs, drain and immerse in ice water.
When cool enough to handle, roll egg to break shells.
Halve eggs lengthwise.
Pop yolks into bowl.
I use a chopper to mash yolks.
Mix mayo and mustard, salt and pepper to taste - enough to just moisten, but keeping the filling from being runny.
Fill whites.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt 5 spoons of butter in heavy saucepan over medium heat. Blend in flour and cornstarch. Stir until smooth. Stir in sugars. Stir until sugars melt and mixture is smooth. Blend in scalded milk, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring until mixture boils after each addition. Vigorously stir about 3 tablespoons hot mixture into egg yolks. Add to hot mixture. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in salt, vanilla and 1 tablespoon butter. Mix well. Pour into pie shell. Beat egg whites until they hold a stiff peak. Put on pie. Bake until brown.

title: pan dirt cake
directions: In a blender or food processor, process cookies until crumbly. Take out 2 tablespoons of crumbs and set aside for topping.

title: pasties(this is a recipe i put together.)
directions: Mix and add enough water to make a dough that can be rolled out.
Divide the dough in 8 or 9 balls and roll out as for pie.

title: potato dumplings(with sauerbraten)
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; cool and peel.
Press through ricer onto towels to dry.
Dry for 1 hour.
Place all ingredients into a large bowl except croutons.
Shape into long roll about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Cut into pieces 1 1/2 inches long.
Place crouton into center of each.
Shape into small balls.
Cook in rapidly boiling water until they rise to the top, then simmer 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Serve with Dumpling Garnish.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In medium saucepan, heat orzo in shortening over medium heat. Bring chicken broth to a boil in another pan. As pasta begins to brown, lower heat. Add butter and rice.
When butter has melted, add salt and broth. Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until broth is absorbed.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil. Let simmer for about 15 minutes. Cool and bottle in ketchup bottles.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Gradually stir in crushed pineapple, 1 cup nuts, onion and salt.
Mold into ball; chill well.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill and serve with party rye and crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Shred cooked, cooled chicken and spread evenly in bottom of baking dish or pan. Mix soups and 1/2 cup chicken broth in saucepan. Cook onions in butter until translucent. Add to soups. Stir until smooth. Pour over chicken. Mix Stove Top stuffing with butter, melted and 1 cup of broth. Spread over chicken. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: *Approximately 2 pounds of fish for 8 people.

title: gram lundy's sugar cookies
directions: Mix eggs, shortening and sugar together.
Add buttermilk, baking soda, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Add flour, but do not make dough too stiff.
Bake at 350°.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix together in a large bucket.
Get out all bubble wands (small and large) you can find.
Enough bubbles for everyone to enjoy.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, egg, Crisco, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Slowly add sour milk or buttermilk, then flour.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and fruit cocktail.
Add salt, soda and flour.
Stir until well mixed, no need to beat.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar with 1 cup peanuts.

title: celery relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: chicken and doritos
directions: Simmer milk, soup and chilies together in saucepan.
Put a layer of Doritos, a layer of cheese and a layer of chicken in casserole dish.
Repeat and end with cheese on top.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breast-of-chicken rustic
directions: (The noodles cook to perfection right in the skillet with the other ingredients.)

title: whole wheat orange quick bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Stir about 75 strokes.
Pour batter in greased pan.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Makes one loaf.

title: banana bread
directions: Cook at 350°, about 1 hour, until pick comes out clean.

title: crispy shrimp salad
directions: Break up lettuce, then combine with onions and celery; mix well ahead of serving for a crunchy, crispy green salad. Immediately before serving, toss shrimp and frozen peas with approximately 1 cup of mayonnaise. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add chow mein noodles and mix again. Serve immediately.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Peel and cut up carrots.
Boil until tender; drain.
Puree in blender or beat with mixer until smooth.
Add butter; blend until butter is melted.
Add all other ingredients until well blended. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sauted apple-toasted walnuts
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, melt butter over low heat.
Toss apples with lime and pulp.
Add apples and saut 3 minutes.
Cover with foil and smother until tender.
Remove apples and place on serving dishes.
Add grape juice, lime peel, maple syrup, vanilla, allspice and nutmeg to the skillet and boil, stirring constantly, until the mixture becomes a syrup, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Toast walnuts by heating them in an ungreased nonstick skillet, stirring with wooden spoon, until they begin to brown and are fragrant. Pour syrup over apples.
Sprinkle with walnuts and serve warm. Makes 4 servings.

title: 3 hour chunk pickles
directions: Wash and chunk the pickles; soak in salt water for 3 hours. Drain.
Add ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Pack in prepared jars.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown ground meat with onion, celery and bell pepper until brown.
Next, add tomato sauce, 1 can water and ketchup.
In separate pot, boil potatoes and carrots until tender.
Add corn, beans, carrots and potatoes to meat.
Slice smoked sausage and add to meat.
Cook all this on low heat for about 30 minutes.
You may have to add more water.
Serves 15.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir with spoon to mix up cocoa.
Make a well in the flour mixture.
Add mayonnaise and buttermilk.
Beat with mixer real well.
Add vanilla; beat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour in dripper pan; bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Frost while still warm.

title: country stew
directions: Cut vegetables and beef in same size chunks.
Put ingredients into a large stew pot in order given.
Cover and cook in 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until all is done.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix together pudding and milk.
Mix everything together.
Makes 1 dish full.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut breast meat into bite size.
Beat eggs and milk together with salt and pepper.
Put meat in egg mixture; let stand at least an hour.
Roll in flour and deep fat fry.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix cornmeal, sour cream, eggs and sugar.
Pour into greased skillet.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Mix in large bowl tomatoes, onions, bell pepper and relish.
Crumble the cooled cornbread and toss into the salad ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and 1 tablespoon sugar; pour over salad and stir.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese over top.
This can be made the night before serving.
If so, do not add the tomatoes, relish and toppings until ready to eat.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together well.
Add pumpkin, applesauce and vanilla; mix.
Mix dry ingredients (sift).
Add dry to liquid mixture.
Mix.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 medium loaves (8 1/2 x 2 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch).

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix and cook in 400° oven until done, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: country cheese soup
directions: heat large soup pot and add butter.
When bubbly, add vegetables and saute until soft, not brown.
Sprinkle flour over them and cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in broth and cream.
Stir until thick and starts to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, pepper and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts. Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: In bowl, with electric mixer at low speed, blend all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Increase speed to high, beat for 2 minutes.
Spoon batter into 18 paper lined 2 1/2-inch muffin pan tins.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean; cool.
In pan, melt chocolate chips.
Using spatula, scoop chocolate into a plastic bag, cut a hole in the corner of the bag.
Drizzle chocolate over cupcakes. Makes 18 cupcakes, 136 calories; 105 mg. sodium; 4 grams fat per cupcake.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Grease a large 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine cream soups and heat until mixed.
Add rice and pour over bottom of baking dish.
Place raw chicken pieces on the rice mixture.
Sprinkle chicken with dry onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Uncover and let brown a little, about 15 minutes.

title: giant soap bubbles
directions: You will need a wire coat hanger, bent to make a circle.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In medium saucepan, heat water and margarine to boiling.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring vigorously, until mixture leaves side of pan. Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until mixture is smooth and glossy.
Spoon 6 mounds, about 3-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Split and remove any filaments of soft dough.
Fill as desired.

title: fast and easy crab dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in pie plate like crust.
Mix crab and red sauce together and spread on top of cream cheese.
Refrigerate! Serve with crackers.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Cube potatoes and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: You will need 20 to 24 wooden popsicle sticks.

title: courtney's pigs in a blanket
directions: Roll hot dog up in crescent roll. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: helen's holiday punch
directions: Make ice ring.
Chill liquid ingredients. Keep ice cream frozen.
Place ice ring in bottom of punch bowl.
Pour in liquids and scoop ice cream on top.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together real good.
Make into balls and put in refrigerator until you get the chocolate ready.

title: eck's christmas cookies
directions: Dredge fruits in 1 cup of flour.
Mix together.
Mix all together; add fruit and nut mixture in last.
Drop by 1 1/2 teaspoons.
Bake 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; boil for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda; pour over the popcorn and salted peanuts in large roasting pan.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread out on a cookie sheet to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: green pea salad
directions: Pour peas into bowl; add egg, water chestnuts, red pepper, onion, celery, mayonnaise, mustard and pepper.
Blend.
Salt to taste.
Cover and chill 8 to 24 hours.
To serve, spoon into lettuce leaves on platter or individual plates.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: parmesan pasta
directions: Cook and boil macaroni until done. Cool macaroni under cold water.
Take rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly.
A nice cold salad for summer.
You can substitute regular Parmesan dressing with a fat-free Parmesan.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first three ingredients together and pour over rice chex.
Cool 10 minutes.
Shake in bag with powdered sugar.

title: sopas de espiritu santo(holy ghost sopas)
directions: Bring water to boil, add meat, and spices tied in a clean cloth, wine, onion, tomato sauce, mint and salt.
Cover and cook until meat is tender, about 3 hours.
Cut cabbage into wedges and add to pot.
Cook until tender.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and boil slowly for 3 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: jan's quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-inch muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 12 rolls.

title: pink perfection cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Mix with dry ingredients, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Drop from teaspoons or roll into balls. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost with Pink Perfection Frosting.

title: cherry-o-cream pie
directions: Whip cream cheese.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour in crust. Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Chill pie filling, then spread on top of pie.

title: breakfast snack
directions: Fry bacon; set aside, crumbled.
Boil eggs; chop.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Halve English muffins.
Mix bacon, eggs and cheese mixture together.
Proportion on each English muffin half.
Place grated cheese (any kind) over each muffin.
Heat in oven at 400° for 10 minutes until cheese melts. Good to freeze.

title: chinese omelettes
directions: Prepare meat and vegetables.
Place in individual bowls and reserve.
Beat 2 eggs for each omelette.
In a wok or skillet, heat 1 teaspoon of the sesame oil.
Add eggs; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons each of meat, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Cook over low heat until omelette is set but moist on top.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.
Roll up and serve.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel carrots; slice and cook in boiling salted water until they are crisp and not overcooked.
You don't have to cook them very long.
Add all the ingredients and refrigerate.
Keeps a long, long time in refrigerator.

title: cranberry freeze
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayo and sugar.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread evenly in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze.
Cut and serve frozen.
Great salad with any meat.

title: cheese-sausage biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll and cut into desired biscuit size.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: classic apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Fit one pie crust into 9-inch pie plate. Set aside. Unfold the other pie crust. Cut into 1-inch wide strips. Combine sliced apples, the 2/3 cup sugar, the apple juice concentrate, cornstarch, lemon juice, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in large bowl. Pour apple filling into crust in pie plate. With pie crust strips, weave a lattice over top of pie. Crimp ends of lattice strips under edge of crust. Brush egg wash over lattice. Sprinkle with the 1 tablespoon of sugar. Bake in 400° oven for 55 minutes. If edges begins to get too dark after 20 minutes, cover them with foil. Let cool on wire rack.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onions lightly in margarine.
Add the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
This is very good when you precook the ribs (beef or pork) in the oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Bake and cool pastry.
In saucepan, combine 1 cup sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and clear.
Add a little hot mixture to egg yolks.
Return all to hot mixture; cook 1 minute more.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter, lemon peel and juice.
Pour mixture into shell.

title: simple sloppy joes
directions: Fry hamburger, drain grease.
Pour in tomato sauce.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Ready to eat.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix cole slaw, shrimp, Crab Delights (shred or cut up first). Add dressing to taste.
Toss Cheddar cheese to taste.
Also, too much cheese will make the salad too rich.
Mix and store in an airtight stainless steel bowl.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Peel and sweeten to taste at least 1 quart of peaches.
I use two 16 ounce bags of Stillwell peaches, thawed with 1 cup sugar. Melt margarine in a large baking dish.
Add the fruit and juice. Mix batter by mixing milk, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Pour batter over fruit and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill in refrigerator overnight. Serve with sticks of carrots, celery, green and red peppers, cauliflower flowerets, cucumber or with chips.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: In a

large glass bowl, make an even layer of the lettuce. Mix onion and celery and sprinkle over. Sprinkle water chestnuts, then unthawed peas. Spread salad dressing evenly over top and sprinkle with sugar.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, layer remaining ingredients over salad dressing.
To serve, layer onto salad plates.

title: fruit bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add bananas and eggs.
Mix until well blended. Add Bisquick and rest of fruit.
Pour into greased loaf
pan.
Bake
in
350° oven and bake for about 55 minutes.
(I check
after 50 minutes and lower temperature to 300° if browning too quickly.)

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add extract.
Pour into three greased and floured (Baker's Joy) 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and place on cake racks and let cool in pans.

title: pretzel torte
directions: Mix
butter,
sugar
and
chopped pretzels together and reserve 3/4 cup for top of torte.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: veggie pizza
directions: On a cookie sheet, flatten crescent rolls, pressing seams together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Beat the cream cheese and dressing; mix together.
Stir in sour cream; spread on cooled crust.
Top with assorted veggies (broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, celery, green and red peppers, if you wish). Spread with grated cheese.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: In a glass baking dish, unroll 1 crescent roll in bottom. Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Spread on bottom crescent roll. Unroll 2nd crescent roll and place on top. Bake at 375° until golden brown. Mix powdered sugar and milk. Pour on top while hot. Serve hot or cold.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
(Do not cook.)
Drain.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise and dry dressing mix.
I sprinkle some seasoning salt on it.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sugar and mix. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Blend well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Add topping, if desired.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onions and green pepper.
Stir in pimento; spread half of mixture in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with half of the cheese and crumbs.
Repeat layers of onions and cheese.
Beat eggs and cream; add salt and pepper and pour over onions.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or
until set.

title: pear butter
directions: Mix and boil about 10 minutes.
Pour into jars.

title: apple cheese salad
directions: Pour hot water over red hots; stir until dissolved.
Add jello and stir.
Stir in applesauce and pour 1/2 the mixture in an 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.
Have cheese at room temperature and blend in nuts, celery and mayonnaise and spread over the firm applesauce mixture.
Pour remaining apple mix over this and chill until firm.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Mix the three ingredients by hand. Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, not touching.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
May be frozen in balls and baked anytime.
Serves lots.

title: chicken with almonds
directions: Cut chicken up into uniform squares.
Place on plate with almonds.
Thinly slice bamboo shoots, water chestnuts and cucumber.
Shred onion.

title: beef goulash(servings: 4)
directions: Heat vegetable oil in a large frypan or Dutch oven.
Add meat cubes and brown well, approximately 10 minutes.
Stir in onions and cook until soft.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic salt, paprika and sugar.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour in hot water; cover and simmer gently, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: championship chili
directions: Brown stew meat and
ground
beef; drain.
Mix the rest of the ingredients, except beans,	and
add to ground beef and beef chunks.
Cut tomatoes very	fine.
Simmer
for 1 hour and then add beans; simmer for
or
more hours, (the longer the better). Remove the bay leaf before serving.

title: coconut patties
directions: Combine sugar, milk and syrup.
Boil until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Cool and whip.
Add coconut, nuts, butter and vanilla. Drop by spoonful or pour in platter. Cool until set.

title: frozen lemon loaf
directions: Line the bottom and sides of an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with foil, extending the foil 1-inch over the edge of the pan.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Cook egg, milk, sugar and vinegar until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Pour over shredded or cubed cheese and mix well.

title: cream cheese deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Reserving whites, remove yolks and place in a blender or food processor.
Add next 8 ingredients. Process until well blended.
Spoon yolk mixture into a pastry bag, fitted with a large star tip.
Pipe into egg white halves. Garnish with parsley and paprika.
Store in an airtight containing in refrigerator.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen deviled eggs.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Add all ingredients in
a large pot.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine
ingredients in order above and mix well.
Form into small
balls and bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 350°
for 20 minutes.
May be frozen before cooking.	Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: chocolate oatmeal crinkles
directions: *Blend together 2 tablespoons hot water, 1/4 cup instant coffee and 1/4 cup corn syrup with the cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture.

title: gook
directions: Put in layers in sprayed casserole dish.
Top with soup and grated cheese.
Bake 2 hours at 350° or until done.

title: apricot preserve cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add preserves. Blend.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Sift flour and cinnamon together. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in chopped apricots and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan in a 325° oven for
1 to 1 1/2 hours. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Mix together flour, yeast and salt in a large bowl.
Cut in butter.
Stir egg yolks and sour cream together and mix into flour mixture.
Knead dough until smooth.
Divide into thirds and chill.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chips.
Stir and pour over cereal.
Mix well.
Put powdered sugar in a large bag or bowl. Add cereal and shake or mix well.

title: corn bread
directions: Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
A very moist corn bread.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes, sugar and Carnation milk.
Cut into small pieces the bitter sweet chocolate and sweet chocolate; melt over hot water with marshmallows.
Stir until all is melted together.
Add vanilla and beat until it thickens.
Pour into large platter or square pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: my mom's rhubarb custard kuchen
directions: Work together first 3 ingredients like pie crust and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up rhubarb and pour into crust.
In bowl, beat eggs, sugar, flour and cinnamon or nutmeg.
Pour over rhubarb and dot with oleo.
Sprinkle corn flakes over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator rhubarb jam
directions: In a large kettle, combine rhubarb and sugar. Stir over medium heat until mixture boils. Turn down heat and cook and stir constantly for 12 minutes. Then add pineapple. Stir and again boil the mixture to a boil and cook for another 3 minutes. Add package of gelatin and stir to dissolve. Pour into hot sterilized jars and cool. Place lids on jars and store in the refrigerator.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until set, about 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno pepper cornbread
directions: Mix together; bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes until brown. Will freeze.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put nuts in baked pie shell and pour syrup mixture over nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple squares (blueberry, cherry, peach...)
directions: Mix sugar and crisco until creamy. Add eggs. Mix flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Alternately put flour and buttermilk into crisco mixture. Separate dough into two parts. Chill in refrigerator before rolling between wax paper sheets. Place half, covering bottom into a large baking dish or jellyroll pan. Pour in filling. Top with remaining rolled - out dough. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together. Beat well. Bake in a greased and floured oblong pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in tightly sealed container.
Place 2 heaping teaspoons in a cup.
Add boiling water.
Stir and enjoy.
Sweeten with sugar or sweetener.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Mix beans, 1/2 pkg. of seasoning mix, and a couple of teaspoons of taco sauce, heat and mix well.
Spread this on a cookie sheet or cake pan.
Let beans cool, you can stick in freezer a few minutes to cool off quicker.	When beans are cooled off, lightly pour taco sauce over beans.
Mix sour cream and other 1/2 pkg. of seasoning mix, spread over beans.
Sprinkle cheese over this.	Layer green peppers, onions, tomatoes and lettuce over cheese.
You can make this the night before, but don't add lettuce and tomatoes until the next day.

title: stew cooked in foil
directions: Fold

pieces of foil in half to double thickness. Shape beef into patty, center on foil, add vegetables. Seal foil by folding. Put on hot coals and turn after 10 minutes. Cook about 20 to 25 minutes longer. This is for one serving.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat with a mixer until smooth.

title: diet 7-up cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as stated on box.
Cool.
Poke holes with fork throughout top of cake.
Prepare the jello.
Substitute cold water with 1 cup diet 7-Up.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: fresh broccoli salad(light)
directions: Trim off large leaves and remove tough ends.
Wash broccoli thoroughly and chop coarsely.
Add onions, eggs and carrots to broccoli.
Toss.

title: biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, ginger, nutmeg, salt and orange peel.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter and shortening until crumbly.
Stir in half and half just until moistened.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth, 1 minute.
Roll out dough to 3/4-inch thickness. With 3-inch star or favorite cutter, cut out biscuits.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Brush tops with melted butter.

title: pear or peach salad
directions: Drain pears; place halves on plate and put 1/4 teaspoon of mayonnaise on each half.
Sprinkle cheese over mayonnaise and top with a cherry if desired.

title: mama's famous apple pie(with buttery flaky pastry dough)
directions: Using a rubber spatula, thoroughly mix in a large bowl first 3 ingredients.
Working quickly to prevent softening, cut into 1/4-inch pieces:
unsalted butter.
Add the butter to the dry ingredients.
Using a pastry blender or two knives, chop the butter into pea sized pieces.
Add shortening or lard.
With a few quick swipes of the pastry blender or rubber spatula, distribute throughout the bowl.
Continue to chop until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs with some pea-sized pieces.
Do not let mixture soften and begin to clump; it must remain dry and powdery.
Drizzle over the flour and fat mixture 1/3 cup plus 1 Tbsp. ice water.
Cut with blade side of the rubber spatula until the mixture looks evenly moistened and begins to form small balls.
If the balls of dough stick together, you have added enough water; if they do not, drizzle over the top:
1 to 2 Tbsp. ice water.
Cut in the water, then press with your hands until the dough coheres.
The dough should look rough, not smooth.
Divide the dough in half, press each half into a round flat disk, and wrap tightly in plastic. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, preferably for several hours, or up to 2 days before rolling.
The dough can be wrapped airtight and frozen for up to 6 months; thaw completely before rolling.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and mix.
Yields 1 1/2 pints.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. This can be made a few days before needed. Excellent with raw vegetables.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn; add nuts and mix together.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour; stirring every 15 minutes.

title: golden layers biscuit taco casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Lightly spray 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Spread taco sauce evenly in bottom of sprayed baking dish.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture, blending well. Stir in 1/2 cup of candies.
Drop by teaspoons on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate tops of cookies with remaining M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage lightly with chopped onion.
Cut up cabbage into bite-size chunks and boil until soft.
Pare potatoes into cubes. Slice carrots 1/4-inch thick.

title: spaghetti hot dish
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse and drain.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch pan. (I spray with Pam.)
Mix egg and milk; pour over spaghetti.
Brown meat, onion and seasonings.
Drain fat.
Pour over noodles.
Pour Ragu over hamburger.
Cover with cheese.
Add pepperoni on top of cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered in foil.

title: pepper steak
directions: Chop onion, pepper and cube steak into bite-size pieces. Marinate the steak in soy sauce for a few minutes or until the steak has soaked up the sauce.
Add onions and peppers to meat and sauce and cook until done.
Serve over rice.

title: fruit cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ice cream.
Stir until melted. Add cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mama's old fashion tea cakes
directions: If you use self-rising flour, leave out salt.
This was Grandma's old fashion "tea cake."
She rolled them out by hand like for biscuits.
But she flattened them out and left her finger prints on them.
I can see them now, where those three fingers left their imprint.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: shoo-fly cake(pennsylvania dutch)
directions: Mix molasses, water and baking soda in large bowl and set aside to cool.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a bowl fine crumbs are formed.
Save about 3 cups of crumbs for topping.
Mix liquid and remaining crumbs together slightly.
Pour into greased pan, 13 1/2 x 10-inch.
Sprinkle with the crumbs you save for topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix soup, chiles, olives and milk; set aside.
Cut tacos into quarters and fry in oil for about 1 minute.
Do not let them get hard.
Layer soup, tacos and cheese in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown ground round and drain off fat.
Add all other ingredients and cook in crock-pot on high for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Can cook in pot on stove for 1 hour on low heat or simmer.

title: grilled smoked turkey 'n muenster sandwiches
directions: Evenly spread Thousand Island dressing on each bread slice. Equally top 3 bread slices with 1/2 of the cheese, turkey, then remaining cheese; top with remaining bread slices, dressing side down.
