Evenly spread butter on outside of bread slices.
In large skillet, cook sandwiches, covered, over medium heat, turning once and pressing down sandwiches occasionally, 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 3 hearty sandwiches.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice (need 4 cups liquid; may need to add additional water, if necessary).
Add jello.
Remove from heat. Stir.
Cut cream cheese and add to jello mixture. Stir in salt. Refrigerate for approximately 2 hours.
Stir in cherries.
Beat whipping cream. Fold into mixture.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve the juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Add enough water to juice to equal 3/4 cup.
Add cornstarch, honey, bouillon, garlic and pepper; set aside.

title: potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients except evaporated milk and chives in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low overnight.
Stir in evaporated milk during last hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Cream well.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Mix well.
Drop with spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: angel food candy
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and vinegar in a heavy gauge saucepan, 2 quart size, and cook medium heat stirring until sugar in dissolved. Place a candy thermometer in the pan and keep on medium heat until it reaches 300°. while waiting for candy to get to the right temperature, grease a jelly roll pan.
When candy is 300 degrees on the thermometer, IMMEDIATELY remove from heat and stir baking soda in quickly with a wooden spoon.
Then pour quickly into pan DO NOT spread.
Let cool 1 hour.
Break into pieces and dip into melted chocolate, set on wax paper to set.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

title: apple butter cake(moist and spicy cake)
directions: Stir together the dry ingredients.
Beat butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Combine buttermilk and apple butter alternately with flour mixture; mix well after each addition.
Pour in greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on cake rack.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Best made the day before.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Sprinkle 1 cup of coarse salt over ingredients.
Cover with ice cubes and let stand for 4 hours.
Drain and rinse well.

title: where's the beef?
directions: Cut and remove top of bread loaf and hollow out the bread, leaving about 1-inch thick sides, reserving the top to be used as a lid. Mix all other ingredients together, seasoning with Worcestershire, Louisiana hot sauce, Tabasco and cayenne to taste.
Put the filling ingredients inside bread.
Top with the bread lid.
Wrap the loaf in foil and bake at 300° on a cookie sheet for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Remove foil.
Take off top of loaf.
Serve on platter. Surround with Fritos or crackers.
Serves 10 to 12.
Round bread keeps filling warm for quite awhile.

title: bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over low until beans are tender.
Great for a cold winter day!

title: brown sauce
directions: Add peppercorns, garlic, thyme, basil, rosemary, bay leaves and beef bass; simmer on low for 3 hours.
Mix flour and water. Wash, then add to stock until it thickens.
Reduce heat for 10 minutes, then strain.

title: whipped strawberry delight
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup liquid.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in juice and water.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
Whip topping mix with milk until soft peaks form.
Whip gelatin until fluffy.
Beat in whipped topping.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Turn into a lightly oiled 5 cup mold.
Chill.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and set aside.
Brown hamburger meat.
Pour half corn bread mixture on bottom.
Sprinkle hamburger, onion and peppers on top.
Then lay slices of Velveeta on this.
Press down and pour rest of corn bread mixture over this layer.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the last 3 ingredients slightly; add 1 cup cold water. Boil until very thick.
Cool.
Gently stir in the berries.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill several hours before serving.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped topping.
Can also be frozen.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Add oleo
and cheese to hot carrots.
Add the remaining ingredients
and mix well.	Place in an 11 x 6-inch casserole. Top with
buttered
bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "no cook" banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix together graham cracker crumbs and 1 1/2 sticks soft margarine and press in 13 x 9-inch glass dish.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and
store
in
jar to use when needed.
Use 2 or 3 teaspoons of mix for each cup of hot water.
Serves 50 people.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain and mash.
Add all ingredients.
Save 1/2 stick butter and put on top.
Spread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for one hour.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Beat eggs with 3/4 cup butter, the melted chocolate and the sugar for 5 full minutes until smooth and thick.
In separate bowl, beat peanut butter with remaining 1/4 cup of butter.
While you are beating, add up to 1/3 cup of the cream in order to make the peanut butter a spreadable consistency that will swirl readily into the chocolate mixture.
Spoon chocolate mixture into pie shell.
Swirl peanut butter into chocolate mixture.
Beat remaining heavy cream until thicken enough to spread across the top of the pie.
Garnish cream with semi-sweet chocolate. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Brush pie shell with small amount of the beaten eggs.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
If using metal pan, bake shell in preheated 450° oven,
until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
If using pie plate, bake shell at 425°.
Cool on wire rack.
Reduce temperature to 375° for metal pan or 350° for pie plate.

title: carrot and sweet onion relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium-size bowl.
Stir well and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, remove bay leaf and drain liquid.
Serve as an accompaniment to grilled poultry. Yields about 2 cups.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in bottom of 3-quart casserole dish.
In large pan, melt butter and slowly blend in flour.
Add the remaining ingredients to the butter/flour mixture.
Stir sauce over low heat until cheese is melted.
Pour sauce over broccoli and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple nut torte
directions: Place in mixing bowl, first 4 ingredients.
Mix with beater until foamy.
In separate bowl, sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add this to sugar mixture.
With wooden spoon, stir nuts and apples to mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While warm, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix ingredients together and then roll into balls (except cinnamon-sugar mixture).
Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix liquid ingredients together.
Add both mixtures together with a spoon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: honey-spice cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix liquids in dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in large greased and floured loaf pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute 1/2 cup chopped onion with 1 stick of butter or margarine. Add all ingredients above together and place in greased 9x13 baking pan and bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: classic greek salad
directions: Wash, cut and chill romaine lettuce to crisp it.
Slice and cut other vegetables.
When ready to serve salad, dry romaine with paper towels.
Combine all vegetables in large bowl.
Top with olives and Feta cheese.

title: sweepsteak
directions: Wrap in double heavy-duty foil; close tightly.
Heat oven to 400°.
Turn to 275°.
Put in 275° oven for 8 hours.

title: crab soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Be careful not to burn.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread on cold cake or bars. Makes enough frosting for a 9 x 13 dessert.

title: mocha pot de creme
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend at top speed.
Pour into glasses.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: peaches and cream cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch deep dish pie pan. Combine the flour, salt, milk, pudding, baking powder, egg and butter in a large mixing bowl; beat for 2 minutes on medium speed. Pour into prepared pan.
Place drained peaches over batter.

title: franke's fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour and mix.
Combine chopped nuts and fruit.
Add soda and cardamom to the 1/2 cup flour.
Add this dry mixture to nuts and fruits and stir to coat.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a saucepan,	heat
butter
and
1/2	cup sugar until melted.
Blend in
flour and remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add eggs
and baking powder.
Mix well with a whisk. Fold in corn.
Turn
into
a
buttered
1 1/2 quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.	Remove casserole from oven and sprinkle with
topping
made of remaining sugar and cinnamon. Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut pie(makes 2)
directions: Beat eggs with spoon and mix with sugar.
Melt 1 stick margarine and stir in.
Stir in vanilla and milk.
Add coconut and mix well.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sallie's broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, salt and pepper and half of cheese.
Stir well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.

title: red and green cole slaw
directions: Combine red and green cabbage and apples in large salad bowl. In small bowl, whisk together mayonnaise and cider vinegar.
Add onion, oregano, salt and pepper.
Stir to combine.
Pour dressing over vegetables and toss.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: mamas egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and add milk.
Beat well then add sugar and vanilla.
Pour into pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 300° and bake 35 more minutes.

title: chinatown chuck roast
directions: Place roast in a plastic bag in a shallow pan.
Combine marinade and pour over meat.
Tie bag closed.
Refrigerate overnight.
Turn over in the morning.
Let stand until evening.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken breasts; save broth.
Dice chicken into desired size chunks.
Cook spaghetti until tender; drain.
Whip cream slightly and stir in undiluted mushroom soup.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in this order:
spaghetti (on the bottom), chicken chunks, Mozzarella cheese, soup and cream mixture.
Repeat layers. Pour up to one cup of chicken broth over the top.
Cover the top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until it bubbles and the top turns golden brown.
Allow it to set for 15 minutes before serving.

title: milk shakes
directions: Blend until frothy.
Add a fresh banana, strawberries or peaches.

title: shrimp, potato and egg omelet
directions: In 4-quart covered pot, mix cooking oil and potatoes.
Smother down until almost tender, then add onions, shallots and bell pepper. Cook until tender. Add shrimp. Cook down until water is cooked out (the shrimp will make water).
In mixing bowl, break eggs. Add 1/4 cup milk to eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add to potato and shrimp mixture.
Mix well.
Cover pot and place in a 350° oven for about 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
(May add 1/2 cup shredded cheese before baking.)

title: date balls
directions: In a saucepan, blend margarine, sugar and dates.
Cook until thick; remove from heat.
Add pecans and cereal.
Form into small balls, about 1-inch and roll in powdered sugar.

title: molly's special turkey stuffing
directions: Mix well.
Stuff turkey loosely.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours and then run for cover because the stuffing will blow that turkey right out of the oven.

title: orange-nut salad
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts; chill.
To serve, stir in nuts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Beat eggs and add other ingredients, mixing by hand.
Pour into oblong pan. Sprinkle a little cheese over top.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust(flaky pie shell for any fruit or berry pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly coat an 8-inch pie pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine 1/2 cup of the unbleached flour with the whole wheat flour in a bowl or in a food processor bowl and add the margarine.
In the bowl, use a fork to crumble the flour and margarine into a coarse mixture.
In the food processor, use the metal chopping blade and pulse the machine 10 to 12 times to cut the margarine into small pieces.
As you form the mixture, add the ice water, one tablespoon at a time, until the lumps appear moist.
Transfer the dough to a board and lightly knead it for 1 minute.
Form into a ball.
Place in a small bowl; cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 10 minutes.

title: almond crescent cookies
directions: With electric mixer, combine unsifted flour, nuts, 1 cup of the sugar, butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Divide dough into 36 balls.
Form into crescent shape.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sift remaining sugar over cookies.

title: light lime broiled chicken
directions: Combine lime juice, garlic, onion and basil in a small dish. Pour over chicken breasts.
Cover and marinate 30 to 60 minutes. Turn chicken over once.
Place chicken on rack in broiler pan (reserve marinade).
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat source for 15 minutes.
Baste twice with marinade.
Turn chicken and repeat. Chicken is done when it is brown and juices run clear when meat is pierced.
Can use grill in place of oven.
Contains 142 calories per serving, 3 grams of fat and 73 mg. cholesterol.

title: soft gingerbread boys
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and molasses thoroughly. Stir in water. Blend dry ingredients with flour and stir into mix. CHILL.

title: date nut cookies
directions: Chop up dates and cook in 1 cup water for 10 minutes.
Add butter, salt and soda.
Add eggs mixing each time, then brown sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Drop by spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken spread
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine all the ingredients and blend well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: pumpkin nut bread(makes two loaves)
directions: Beat eggs in large mixer bowl on medium speed until combined. Add pumpkin, sugar, brown sugar, water and oil; beat until well blended.
Combine flour, dry milk, wheat germ, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in large bowl.
Beat into pumpkin mixture on low speed; stir in nuts and spoon into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf dishes.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until wood pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar, salt and soda.
Make 3 wells in these dry ingredients.
In one well, put melted shortening.
In second well, put the vanilla.
In third well, put the vinegar.
Pour water over entire mixture.
Beat thoroughly with fork.
Bake in square baking dish for 40 minutes at 350°.
Bake cupcakes for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecued pork platter
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl and marinate 15 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat barbecue at high and oil grill.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Use a glass 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt oleo.
Add to hash browns along with sour cream, onions and soup.
Also you can mix cheese and sprinkle some on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: louisiana shrimp
directions: Peel, devein and rinse shrimp.
Mix together all ingredients except for the shrimp.
Pour over shrimp and marinate several hours.
Place lettuce on individual plates and spoon on shrimp mixture.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: salmon biscuit roll
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Measure oil in cup and add enough milk to make 2/3 cup, but do not stir.
Add oil mixture all at once to sifted ingredients and stir to make a smooth dough.
Roll out on lightly floured board to 9-inch square.
Spread salmon down center about 3-inches wide.
Cover with sides and invert on baking sheet. Cut slashes in top crosswise.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Serve with celery soup, mushroom or tomato soup.

title: swedish green potatoes
directions: Beat potatoes, cream, sugar, butter, salt and pepper until fluffy.
Add herbs and beat.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, including 1 package pudding, in large bowl and mix well with electric mixer for 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool completely, then frost with the following:

title: chocolate gook
directions: Whip whipping cream stiff and set aside; add vanilla.
Beat egg whites real stiff and set aside.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips.
Mix in egg yolks and sugar.
Blend together. It will get very thick.
Add egg whites and mix well.
Fold in cream and mix well. Fold in cake and pour into loaf pan to chill. Refrigerate.

title: coffee punch
directions: Stir hot coffee and sugar until dissolved.
Allow to cool. Add milk and vanilla and stir well.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatine into soup (might have to warm up).
Put in salad dressing and cream cheese.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Chill in mold.

title: artichoke and spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach and artichokes (if frozen) according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Drain artichoke hearts.
Combine garlic, oil and vinegar.
Pour over artichokes.
Melt butter and stir in flour.
Gradually add half and half, stirring constantly with a wire whisk.
Add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Add spinach, salt and pepper.
Remove artichokes from marinade and place in bottom of a small buttered casserole. Cover with spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/8 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli crawfish casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in butter.
Add crawfish tails and cook on low for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup.
Mix in rice and broccoli.
Put in casserole dish and cover with seasoned bread crumbs with pat of butter on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rainbow ice cream dessert
directions: Tear cake into bite size pieces.
Divide into thirds in 3 separate bowls.
Sprinkle a different jello over each.
Toss lightly with fork until cake is well coated.
Place strawberry cake pieces in bottom of 10-inch tube pan.
Spoon strawberries over cake.
Spread 1/3 of ice cream over strawberries.
Repeat layers with lime cake pieces, crushed pineapple, ice cream, orange-pineapple cake pieces, orange slices and ice cream.

title: veg-a-roni
directions: Mix all together and bake until done.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Cube bread and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Cook sausage until well done.
Drain and place over bread; add mushrooms.
Beat eggs and milk, liquid from mushrooms and Worcestershire sauce and pour over bread and sausage. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
This is important so milk and egg mixture will soak into the bread.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen, also can be reheated after cooking.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs, apples and nuts.
Mix before adding dry ingredients (mix the flour and soda together first). Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a 9 x
13-inch greased pan.

title: holiday mold
directions: Mix all ingredients except sour cream and fruit.
Allow to chill and partially set.
Fold in 2 cups sour cream.
Place fruit in bottom of oiled mold.
Pour in mixture.
Refrigerate until set, overnight or 6 hours.
Use as a salad with meal.
Pour into large plate and enjoy.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Melt butter and mix in Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, and hot sauce.	Pour over pecans.
Stir and salt lightly.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until thick.
Pour over macaroni and cooked vegetables.

title: hot chicken salad(from my sister, filomena)
directions: Mix
all ingredients except cheese and croutons.
Place in large casserole dish (9 x 13-inches).
Sprinkle cheese and croutons
on top.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wassetti
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Cook noodles and drain. Mix soups and add to meat mixture.
Put in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: spicy christmas dip
directions: When cheese has melted, pour in Ro-Tel and mix well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, oats, baking powder and soda in mixer bowl; add margarine, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla and beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Drop by the teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°
for 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool on wire rack.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: crock-pot chicken soup
directions: Put chicken on bottom of crock-pot.
Layer other ingredients on top.
Pour on tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on medium-high for 5 hours.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: In a small bowl, sprinkle gelatin over cold water.
Stir.
Set aside a few minutes to soften.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.

title: stuffed baked potato
directions: Scoop out potato; mash with skim milk.
Add Molly McButter to taste.
Add grated cheese.
Add any chopped vegetable.
Fill shell and bake until browned.

title: microwave picante fish
directions: Cook vegetables first in chicken broth, in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and cook at 100% for 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir once. In an 8 x 8-inch microwavable dish, place fish in a layer.
Cook, covered, at 100% for 4 to 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Drain juices with slotted spoon.
Place vegetables over fish.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Pour salsa over.
Microwave, uncovered, 1 to 2 minutes, until heated.
Sprinkle on cheese. Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry filled stuffing ring
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and celery and saute until tender.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, combine next 6 ingredients.
Stir in onion mixture, eggs and chicken broth and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: corn croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by spoonful into deep fat. Fry until lightly golden.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a heavy roaster, brown flour in oil to make a dark roux. Add onions, green onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute until limp.
Add tomato paste and mix well.
Add tomatoes with liquid, tomato sauce, cayenne, Tabasco, bay leaf, sugar, Worcestershire and lemon juice; simmer 1 hour.
Add shrimp and cook until done, about 10 minutes.
Adjust salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice.
Sprinkle with parsley.
This tastes best if prepared the day before.

title: patio party mix
directions: Melt butter in electric frypan at 200°.
Stir in seasonings. Blend well.
Add Chex, pretzels and nuts.
Mix until coated. Cover skillet, leaving lid vent open.
Heat at 250° for 15 minutes.
Stir midway.
Cool on absorbent paper.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Fry and drain sausage and onion; put into crock-pot.
Prepare Velveeta cheese, chopped tomatoes, cream of chicken soup and whole milk.
Add to cooked sausage and heat.
Serve with Tostitos chips or your choice of chips.

title: coconut pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Open cake mix; put it in the bowl. Add water, eggs and oil.
Add the coconut pecan icing into cake mix; stir until completely mixed up.
Pour the mix in a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes; ovens vary.
Let the cake cool completely, then ice the cake with the Cool Whip.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain grease.
Add all seasonings and tomato sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions; drain.
Spoon small amount of sauce into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer noodles, sauce, Mozzarella cheese, and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: scampi with linguini
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add oil, garlic, lemon juice, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper, oregano, basil, tarragon, salt and 2 tablespoons parsley; mix well.
Simmer over low heat until garlic is just blond; turn off heat.
Dip each shrimp in mixture and arrange, flesh side up, in foil-lined pan. Add wine to skillet.
Bring to boil; simmer until liquid has reduced by 1/4.
Spoon some of the sauce over each shrimp.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs, half and half and seasonings.
In 9 x 13 pan layer the hash browns and sausage.
Pour egg mixture over the hash browns and sausage mixture.
If you want, add cheese in layers. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done and golden brown.

title: quick 'n easy salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 tablespoons of juice.
In medium bowl, mix salmon, egg and onion until sticky.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to salmon juice; mix well, will be foamy.
Add to salmon mixture, mixing well.
Drop with a spoon into hot Crisco and fry until golden brown, turning once.

title: almond crescent cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, 1 cup powdered sugar, vanilla and almond extract; mix well.
Gradually add flour.
When thoroughly blended, add walnuts.
Blend well.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Let cool 30 minutes.
Add bananas, lemonade, orange and pineapple juices.
Freeze.
Let stand until slushy.
Add Fresca or 7-Up.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Saute onion in butter.
Drain and quarter artichokes.
Mix all together.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 7-up lime salad
directions: Put boiling water on top of jello and cream cheese and stir until blended, add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve. Change with orange jello and orange soda.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well with mixer.
Add cream cheese; beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: southwestern spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in the taco seasoning, spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and olives.
Drain spaghetti;
stir into the beef mixture.

title: joan's oven beef stew
directions: Combine tapioca, sugar and salt and mix with the tomato juice. Put meat (cut in pieces) in bottom of casserole dish.
Put sliced vegetables on top.
Pour tomato juice mixture over all.
Cover tightly and bake at 250° for 4 hours.
Do not open!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cakebox cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in salted water, but do not overcook.
Drain and cool.
Add chopped vegetables and dressing.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy cake
directions: Layer in pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: pineapple-marshmallow salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Break up cream cheese and pour some of juice (pineapple) on cheese and beat until smooth (I thin this out quite a bit).
Add mayonnaise.
Place pineapple on marshmallows while thinning out cream cheese.
Place cream cheese mixture on top of pineapple-marshmallow mixture.
Fold in whipped cream (whipped).
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine whole and cream-style corn and eggs.
Add mixture of sugar, cornstarch, salt, dry mustard and minced onion.
Stir in milk and butter.
Pour into 3-quart casserole (greased).
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, stirring once.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Add vegetables to boiling water along with salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Make white sauce of oleo, flour and milk.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add to vegetables and water.
Stir in bacon.
Heat, but do not boil.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: josie's sauerkraut
directions: Drain sauerkraut, rinse well, squeeze out all of the water. Put into saucepan.
Cover with just enough water to cover the sauerkraut.

title: pork chop - potato bake
directions: Brown chops in lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream and pepper.
Gently stir in thawed potatoes, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of onions.

title: homemade bread or parker house rolls
directions: Note:
Sugar and shortening should be the same amount.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add garlic, onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add pepperoni, mushrooms and spaghetti sauce.
Mix and simmer.
Cook pastas in separate pans. Drain.
Layer 1/2 of pastas in a large (11 x 15-inch) casserole dish.
Pat 1/2 of meat and sauce on top; then add 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat process.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserle
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package. Cook broccoli until tender (cool). Place cooked rice in ovenware. Mix in onion, soups, and velveeta until blended well. Cut up broccoli and stir in. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: crab dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kielbasa stew
directions: Lightly brown the kielbasa in a Dutch oven over medium heat; drain.
Stir in celery, onion and carrot.
Cook about 5 minutes more.
Add beans, broth, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle top with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbling and crumbs are browned.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add milk, then fruit mixture and nuts.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the elbow macaroni in salted, boiling water until tender. Drain.
Layer cheese and macaroni in a greased baking dish. Pour enough milk to cover mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or all milk is cooked out.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk (1/2 cup milk with 2 teaspoons vinegar).
Sift in remaining ingredients except zucchini.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cook and stir beef, onion and garlic in oil until beef is browned; drain.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups water, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, salt, paprika, mustard and red pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix by hand.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll in balls 3/4 to 1-inch. Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Use toothpick to pick up balls to dip in chocolate.
Let drain on cookie sheet lined with wax paper and cool.

title: microwave crispy treats
directions: Place butter and peanut butter in a medium bowl.
Microwave 30 seconds to 1 minute on High or until butter is melted.
Add marshmallows.
Mix well.
Microwave 2 to 2 1/2 minutes on High or until all marshmallows melt when stirred. Stir twice during cooking time. Add cereal.
Mix well until cereal is coated.
Press out on waxed paper or into utility dish.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.
Yields 18 to 24 bars.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Bake cake according to boxed directions.
Cake should be baked in a sheet cake pan.
Mix pudding according to boxed directions. Punch small holes in cake; spread pineapple and juice over cake. Then pudding, followed by Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: raspberry ribbon pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir gelatin and boiling water until crystals are dissolved.
Add the frozen berries and lemon juice.
Stir until berries thaw.
Cover and refrigerate until the mixture mounds when dropped with a spoon.

title: chili as you like it
directions: Cook onion and green peppers in oil until soft.
Add ground beef and brown.
Pour in tomato sauce; add chili powder and salt. Boil with cover over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix slowly; don't smash peas.
Cut cheese into cubes.
Chop eggs.
Add to the peas.
Pour mayo and mustard mixture over salad and blend thoroughly.
Best if made the night before.

title: fudge pie
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar.
Blend
in melted chocolate. Add flour,
slightly
beaten
eggs,
salt and vanilla and beat slightly.
Stir in pecans.	Spread in a hot greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at
300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edge is dry. Let cool
in pan.
Serve warm topped with ice cream.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: broccoli ham rolls
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan. Add flour and stir well. Cook until blended.
Gradually add milk and cook until bubbly and thick. Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Place 3 stalks broccoli in each slice of ham.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cover with cheese sauce.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple snacks
directions: Cut the apples in eight pieces.
Spread peanut butter on the apples.
Then serve.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Blend soup and milk. Pour over all.
Top with cheese. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour Bundt pan or use cooking spray.
Pour cake mix into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix very well.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: kung pao chicken
directions: Mix vinegar, soy sauce and sugar; set aside.
Coat chicken with cornstarch.
Heat oil in large skillet or wok.
Add chicken and stir-fry 5 to 7 minutes, until cooked.
Remove from pan and add onion, garlic, red pepper, and ginger; stir-fry 15 seconds. Add wine vinegar mixture and chicken, stirring to coat chicken. Mix in peanuts and serve over rice.

title: cissy's cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix chopped onions and meat with cream cheese.
Shape into a ball.
Serve chilled with crackers.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Note:
For large can of chilies, double recipe.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first three ingredients, then add other ingredients and mix well.
Drop from tablespoon or roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 minutes. Remove from oven while still somewhat soft and let cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Mix in frozen strawberries.
Chill until partly set.
Break angel food cake into pieces.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding and ice cream (softened).
Pour ice cream mixture over cake, then pour jello mixture over cake and ice cream mixture.
Chill until ready to eat.

title: date nut pinwheels
directions: Boil dates, sugar (1/4 cup), salt and water for 5 minutes. Cool.
Add nuts.
Cream the butter, brown sugar and white sugar. Add egg; mix.
Add vanilla, flour and soda.
Chill.
Roll out fairly thin.
Spread with date mixture; roll up tight.
Freeze and slice.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: party sauce appetizer
directions: Combine ground round, Velveeta and sausage.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spread on party rye, (can be frozen). Broil 5 minutes when serving.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs separately, beat well.
Mix other ingredients (except ice and salt) together, then add eggs.
Mix thoroughly. Add to 2-quart ice cream container.
Fill halfway up with regular milk, then put in ice cream bucket layer of ice, layer of rock salt until filled to the top.
Turn on ice cream freezer.
Freeze 20 to 30 minutes until completely frozen.

title: holiday fruit bars
directions: Cream butter; add 1 cup sugar and cream until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add sifted dry ingredients, nuts and fruits.
Mix well and spread batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Let stand until cold or overnight.
Then cut in 3 x 1-inch bars and roll each bar lightly in very fine granulated sugar (store in airtight container).
(Try scissors in hot water to cut fruit.)
Keeps well, if hidden!

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and spread in baking dish. Combine soup, Miracle Whip, lemon juice and salt.
Pour over chicken mixture and lightly stir.
Sprinkle with chips and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: country ham and red-eye gravy
directions: Heat a few drops of oil in a large skillet until skillet is medium-hot.
Lay ham slices in skillet.
Cook on one side for 8 minutes over medium-high heat.
Turn slices and fry 8 minutes more. Pour coffee into skillet with ham slices.
Sprinkle with sugar and stir.
Cover and let simmer over very low heat for 5 to 10 minutes. Serve ham and red-eye gravy together.

title: yam-brosia
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of sweet potatoes and bananas. Set aside.

title: monkey bread(italian)
directions: Melt butter; add cheese and spices.
Dip biscuits in mixture; place in baking dish.
Pour remaining mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Great with soups!

title: halibut casserole
directions: Marinate halibut with white wine for 2 hours.
Cover bowl with Saran Wrap.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and onions.
Remove halibut from marinade.
Pat dry.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Place halibut in a single layer in low baking dish.
Spread above mixture over fish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 500° for 15 to 20 minutes. (Optional:
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup grated cheese.)
Do not overcook!!
Another Alaskan treat.

title: hash brown potato bake
directions: Mix all except 1/2 cheese; spread in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Remove foil; bake 15 minutes.

title: tamale balls
directions: Combine ground beef, 1/2 tablespoon chili powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt, corn meal and 1/2 cup enchilada sauce.
Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch or smaller balls.
Place in skillet and cook until done.

title: quick peppermint ice cream cake
directions: Cut cooled cake into 4 layers. Use rows of toothpicks to cut even slices. Chop chocolate patties and nuts. Soften ice cream slightly. Stir in candy, nuts and peppermint extract. Keep in freezer until a few minutes before serving.

title: nana's microwaved macaroni and cheese
directions: In medium saucepan, combine salt, dry mustard and pepper; stir in milk until smooth.
Add butter.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium-high heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheese until melted.
Add elbows.
Turn into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Microwave until hot. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars and Eagle Brand milk in double boiler.
Add 1 quart whole milk.
Let cool.
Add 5.5 ounce can chocolate syrup. Make up the day before freezing.
Put in refrigerator.
Put in ice cream freezer; add whole milk to freezer line and freeze.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening; add yeast and buttermilk to dry ingredients.
Knead enough to hold together.
Roll dough 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick, cut with biscuit cutter and fold in half.
Dough may be chilled or frozen for later use.

title: linguini salad
directions: Mix and store overnight in refrigerator.

title: sausage bread loaf
directions: Cut loaves of bread in half and allow to rise (follow directions on package).
Brown ground meat and remove excess grease.
Cut sausage in 1/8-inch slices and brown; remove excess grease.
Grate cheese (Mozzarella and Cheddar).
Cut onion tops. Each ingredient should be in individual bowls.
Allow meat to cool.

title: sarwars' bhendi(fried okra)
directions: Wash the fresh okra under cold running water and with a small sharp knife, scrape skin to remove fuzz on surface (frozen needs only to be defrosted and drained).
Pat dry with paper towels.
In a heavy 10 to 12-inch skillet, heat the oil over medium heat.
Add the onion and salt and stir for 7 or 8 minutes, or until brown. Add okra, cumin and pepper and continue to fry, stirring constantly, for 25 minutes or until okra is tender and liquid is gone.
(Frozen okra will be sticky.
Cook longer to dry up liquid.) Serves 4.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown meat.
Drain and add to sauce.
Mix egg, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
In a large baking dish, spread several spoonfuls of sauce; then alternate layers of noodles, sauce and cheese filling, ending with meat sauce on top. Be sure all noodles are covered.
Sprinkle with the rest of the Parmesan cheese.
Pour tomato juice over top until you see it all around edge.
Seal with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil the last 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce in a large Tupperware bowl.
Layer rest of ingredients except bacon and mayonnaise.
Top with mayonnaise. Fry bacon crisp.
Crumble on top.
Pat lid on bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: cream puffs
directions: Boil water, salt and margarine in saucepan.
Add flour and beat.
Remove from heat; add 1 egg, beat and then add second egg. Beat until smooth.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until dry at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave puffs inside until oven cools to finish baking.
Cool before filling with pudding.
Makes 8.

title: lori's fabulous frito pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer 2 cups chips, 1 cup cheese and chili.
Top with remaining chips.
Bake 20 minutes; sprinkle with remaining cheese in the final 5 minutes. Garnish with sour cream and olives.
Serves 5.

title: pasta with marinated tomatoes and basil
directions: * Add more basil if you wish.

title: fruitcake
directions: Add first five ingredients together.
In a large bowl, alternate small amount of cherries, pineapple and pecans.
Sift a small amount of flour after each, until all is covered.
Shake bowl after each layer.
With a wooden spoon, stir in creamed mixture, gently.

title: lebanese or syrian potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; peel and cube.
Add all ingredients and mix gently but thoroughly.
Add more lemon and oil to taste.

title: sweet potato pie(with streusel topping)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat sweet potatoes, milk, egg and spices until smooth.
Pour into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with topping. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: candy bar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Loosen warm cake from sides of pan and invert onto a sugared plate.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until tender.
Drain.
Combine in bowl other ingredients and add raisins.
Mix well.
Pour into ungreased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel custard pie
directions: Beat egg yolks (save whites) and add brown sugar and melted butter.
Mix well.
Add flour and milk and beat well.
Add two beaten egg whites.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in very hot oven until set.

title: antipasto salad platter
directions: Pour dressing over combined pepperoni, beans, tomatoes, cucumbers and mushrooms.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator several hours.
Drain, reserving dressing.
Arrange lettuce on serving platter; top with vegetable mixture.
Serve with dressing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put eggs, onion, salt, flour, baking powder and 1/2 cup potatoes in blender or food processor. Process on low speed until potatoes have gone through blades. Stop and add remaining potatoes. Process on high speed only until all potato cubes have passed through blades. Use a spatula to guide potatoes if necessary. Do not overblend. Should see shreds of potato. Spoon onto a hot well-greased skillet.
Cook until golden brown on both sides over medium heat.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in the microwave. Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour. Place in 9 x 13 x 2 pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: cocktail balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form into small meat balls.
Brown on all sides in 1/4 cup of shortening.
Pour off shortening.

title: banana split cake
directions: In two-quart casserole, arrange in single layer half of the cookies, half of the bananas, half of the glaze and half of the whipped topping.
Repeat with second layer.
Drizzle syrup over. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Just before serving, sprinkle with peanuts.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a large roasting pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rusty's snapper fingers
directions: Mix margarine or butter, white wine and lime juice together in a cup. Grease bottom of baking dish (size of dish depends on number of servings or you can use individual dishes). Cover bottom of dish with thinly sliced tomatoes (peel fresh ones first). Sprinkle the bread crumbs over tomatoes (generous amount to cover tomatoes). Place fish on top of bread crumbs. Warm the margarine (butter) mixture to melt and keep it mixed together while you pour over fish. Salt and pepper lightly. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 500° for 11 to 12 minutes. If fillets are 3/4 inch thick, bake for 15 to 17 minutes.
Individual baking dishes are super hot, warn guests.

title: lemon poppy seed cookies
directions: Combine the flour, salt and poppy seed.
Grate 2 tablespoons of the yellow zest from the lemons.
Beat the butter, zest and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.

title: mexican salsa dip
directions: Put cheese dip in with salsa dip and stir. Put in sour cream and stir until orange-red.

title: leftover potato or bean patties
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil.
Heat oil in frying pan. Drop mixture into pan to fry lightly brown. It is very good.

title: black-olive-and-rosemary bread(for bread machine)
directions: All ingredients must be room temperature. Liquid ingredients should be approximately 80°. Add ingredients in the order specified in your bread machine owners manual.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in salt water until tender.
Brown sausage and drain.
Saute onion in olive oil and add to eggplant and sausage. Combine mushroom soup seasoned with salt and pepper.
Add cracker crumbs.
Place mixture into a casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Bake pie crust.
Put strawberries in crust. Pour mixture over strawberries.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cut fish into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.

title: louisiana shrimp
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter and saute onion and green pepper about 5 minutes or until tender.
Add water, stir in soup mix until thick.
Cover.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and simmer until pink, about 2 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round 8-inch pans. Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla; beat at 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer, scraping constantly. Add eggs; beat 2 minutes more.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Ice.

title: southern yam casserole
directions: Butter baking dish.
Mix all ingredients except marshmallows. Place 1/2 of mixture in dish; dot with marshmallows, then add remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; dot with marshmallows.
Bake 10 more minutes or until brown.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Saute butter, onion and garlic.
Add parsley, oregano and bread crumbs.
Drain 2 cans of juice from clams.
Add clams and 1 can of juice, lemon and Tabasco sauce.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese.
Place in casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot on crackers.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring margarine, water and salt to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Then add flour all at once.
Keep stirring until it comes away from sides of pan.
Remove pan from heat and beat in eggs, one at a time and beat until mixture is smooth.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Flatten shell with fingers before filling.

title: joe's mixed-up veggies
directions: Saute onions in bacon drippings in a saucepan.
When onions are clear, pour can of black-eyed peas and drained corn on top and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes over medium-low heat.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain juices from cherries and pineapple.
Measure 1 1/2 cups; bring to a boil and pour over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved. Measure remainder of juice and add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add to gelatin.
Add fruits and stir well.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.

title: sirloin steaks
directions: Cook steaks in oven at 325° until done.
Chop or slice the vegetables and boil until tender.
Cook the tomatoes in a separate pan until heated.
Add the Italian dressing to the tomatoes and simmer.
Drain steaks and place in a casserole dish over tomatoes. Drain vegetables and place equal amounts on each steak.
Spoon tomatoes and remaining sauce over steaks.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix cookies and butter and press into 9-inch pie plate.
Mix other ingredients and pour into pie.
Freeze at least 4 hours. (Double for 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: delicious sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs and margarine. Add sugar, flour, salt, soda, oil and vanilla.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: patriotic jello dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on package. Pour into glass casserole or baking dish. Refrigerate until set. Spread container of Cool Whip on Jell-O. Spread blueberry pie filling on Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: barf beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Slice kolbassi. Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Garnish with bacon strips.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Uncover last 1/2 hour until nicely browned.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in melted butter.
Add chicken broth and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in milk and seasonings; allow to heat.
Thicken by adding 3 tablespoons cornstarch dissolved in 6 tablespoons water.
Top with freshly chopped parsley.
Serves approximately 6.

title: country biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add water and shortening and beat to a shiny consistency.
The dough will be stiff enough to pour out on floured board or foil.
Sprinkle with flour.
Pat out with hand to 1-inch thick.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet or pan.
Cover top of biscuits lightly with bacon drippings or melted butter.
Heat oven to 400°; bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 23 to 30.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In large pot, cover bone with water.
Add tomatoes, chopped onion, chopped celery and chopped cabbage.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Boil about 1 hour, then remove bones.
Add mixed vegetables and diced potatoes.
Boil until tender.
When vegetables are almost tender, add noodles.
You do not have to add noodles, they are optional.
Makes about 3 gallons of soup.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Fold in pecans.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Place slices in skillet with small amount of bacon drippings.
Cover and fry over low heat.
Turn potatoes over once or twice.
Cook until lightly browned.
(If sweet potatoes are from a new crop, you may want to sprinkle sugar over the slices just before serving.)

title: eutha clark's sourdough banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas and sourdough. Mix after each addition.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Mash ham with fork, mix all ingredients together.
Make into a ball and refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Stir in 1 cup of whole wheat bread mix.
Add banana and nuts.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups bread mix and blend to form a soft dough ball.
Turn out onto a floured surface and cover by inverting bowl.
Let rest 10 minutes. Proceed with knead step.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Combine bread crumbs, onion and about half of the eggs and chopped giblets in large mixing bowl.
Pour broth over ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Place chicken and remaining eggs on top.
Pour soup over chicken.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by package directions but slightly undercook; drain.
Arrange in a greased 3-quart (9 x 13-inch) baking dish. Arrange some of the broccoli florets around the edge of the casserole.
Arrange chicken over broccoli.
Combine undiluted soup, milk, lemon juice, mayonnaise, curry powder and cheese spread over mixture in casserole.
Combine stuffing mix, bread crumbs and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 10.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve hard-cooked eggs lengthwise and remove yolks. Place yolks in a bowl and mash thoroughly with a fork. Add mustard, Miracle Whip and vinegar. Mix well. Season with salt and pepper, if desired. Stuff egg white halves with mixture. Garnish with paprika, if desired.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift sugar, flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Stir
in raisins and nuts.
Add eggs; mix thoroughly. Spread into 15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inch pan sprayed gently with Pam spray.
Spread into pan to cover entire pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° about 20 minutes. Cut into squares while warm.
Sprinkle gently with powdered sugar.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets.
Thinly slice onion into rings.
Take beet juice and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over beets.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: whipped cream dressing for fruit salad
directions: Beat eggs well in top of double boiler.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add pineapple and lemon juices and mix well.
Put over boiling water and cook until spoon is coated, as in making custard.
When cool, it will be thick. Whip 1/2 pint of whipping cream. Fold into mixture.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: monster cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter and peanut butter.
Add eggs, sugars, vanilla, corn syrup and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal, M&M's and chocolate chips.
Use hands to mix or large spoon.
Use ice cream scoop to measure dough (level).
Place 6 cookies on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes; 18 minutes if you like them chewy.

title: hot pepper chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake cake mix for 15 minutes.
Remove
from
oven.
Mix	pudding,
milk	and
cream cheese.
Spread on the top of cake.
Spread pie filling on the top of pudding	mixture and top with Cool Whip and nuts if you like.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until bubbly.

title: madison's french toast sticks
directions: Beat egg, milk, pancake syrup and vanilla. Dip each stick into mix. Cook in preheated skillet with a small amount of oil - till lightly browned on both sides. Spread butter on top of each stick, cut into bites and dip into powdered sugar.

title: spicy bean dip
directions: Combine black beans, garlic, tomato, onion, chillies, hot sauce and cilantro together in a food processor. Blend mixture until smooth. Place mixture in a small baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Heat oven to 350 degrees and warm dip for 10 - 15 minutes. Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: reuben-ata.
directions: Over medium heat, melt oleo, in a large saucepan.
Stir in cabbage and caraway seed.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes (or until well done).
Remove from heat.
Add bread crumbs, cheese and corned beef; lightly toss together.
Turn into 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the sugar and milk and boil 3 minutes, then remove from heat.
Stir in the peanut butter and crackers.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on buttered foil, wax paper or cookie sheet.

title: rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.

title: ruby's cream cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco; add eggs one at a time.
Stir in part of flour and buttermilk; mix all together.
Bake at 350° until done in center.
Bake in 3 layers.

title: egg and biscuit casserole
directions: Mix
Bisquick or similar mix with 1 cup milk and pat in bottom of pan.
Pour over bottom mixture in pan and bake in 350° oven until browned lightly.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: swedish coconut balls
directions: Cream butter, shortening, vanilla, sugar and salt well; then add flour and bakers ammonia (powder with mortar and pestle, can be purchased at Pharmacy).
Mix well.
Form in walnut size balls. Place on unoiled cookie sheet 2 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 325° for 17 to 18 minutes.
Do not open oven door.
Can use color in these.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Let cool 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: deep dish pizza casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add green pepper; mix lightly.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce, mushrooms and onions.
Spoon dinner mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole, top with beef mixture.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Bake in microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: old-fashioned doughnuts
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Beat egg; then add shortening, vanilla and milk.
Beat together for 30 seconds.
Add dry ingredients; beat until smooth.
Brush doughnut maker with light coating of vegetable oil and fill with batter.
Hold doughnut maker over oil at surface and release ring of batter onto surface.
Deep fat fry at 375° (medium) approximately 1 minute on each side, turning to brown evenly.
Remove from oil and drain on paper towels.
Roll doughnuts in cinnamon/sugar when done.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: hamburger soup(serves 6)
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
When pink is gone, add water. Bring to boil and add noodles and corn.
When noodles are done, so is soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: imitation crab meat casserole
directions: If using fresh broccoli, parboil in salted water for 5 minutes first.
Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Add desired amounts of crab meat and mushrooms.
Mix milk and mushroom soup and pour over crab and broccoli.
Top with cheese slices and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour in pie shells. Refrigerate.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all together all ingredients and chill.
Garnish with orange slices and serve.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, drain and reserve 2 tablespoons of grease. Boil potatoes until tender, peel if desired, and cut into bite sized pieces. Meanwhile, saute onions in reserved grease until lightly browned, add flour, sugar, vinegar and water. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add potatoes and crumbled bacon and mix well. Season with salt and pepper. Serve warm or cold.

title: squash casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and green peppers.
Drain and lay half the hamburger, then yellow squash.
Next, add the other half of the hamburger, then the zucchini squash.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: taco supreme salad
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet. Add seasoning mix. Cool in the refrigerator. Mix all salad ingredients, then add hamburger. Do not add chips and dressing until the last minute.

title: lime salad
directions: Bring Jell-O and fruit cocktail to boiling point.
Add cream cheese.
When almost cold, fold in the whipped cream.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix beef with all ingredients.
Split the buns and spread each half with beef mixture, being sure to cover to the edge of the bun.
Place under the broiler about 3-inches from heat. Broil about 5 minutes.
Remember to leave the oven door ajar. Remove from oven and top each piece with 2 strips of cheese. Return to broiler until cheese melts.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage, onion and green pepper in skillet until sausage is done, drain well.
Combine sausage mixture and remaining ingredients except cheese.
Spoon mixture into casserole dish. Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Place egg yolks in food processor and process until fine.
Add several spoons of mayonnaise and mustard and dash of pepper and some dill pickle juice.
Process until smooth.
Adjust seasoning to your taste.
(Suggested:
Several dashes of hot sauce or chili pepper.)
Put yolk mixture into a pastry bag with a medium tip and fill egg white halves.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing. Precook zucchini and onion.
Drain and mix with sour cream and soup.
Put 2/3 of package of stuffing mix in layer on bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Spread zucchini mix over stuffing.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Pat down into zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together and cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir at all times.
Top with meringue.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Melt chocolate over boiling water.
Stir until smooth.
Take off of heat, but leave chocolate over hot water.
Dip fruit pieces in chocolate and cool on a cookie sheet in refrigerator.

title: mushroom almond rice
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add rice and continue cooking until golden.
Add water and bouillon cubes. Stir well.
Heat to boiling.
Cover pan; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Saute almonds and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter; add black pepper.
When rice is tender, add almond and mushroom mixture and mix together.

title: ramp corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Beat eggs and milk together. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake in a greased 10-inch iron skillet in preheated oven at 400° for about 40 minutes.

title: surprise dessert
directions: Mix flour and butter with hands, add nuts; mix well.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix together.
Form into cookies and bake at 350°.

title: microwave hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook everything except butter and vanilla 1 1/2 minutes.
Then add margarine and cook 1/2 minute or 15 seconds.
When to desired consistency, add vanilla.
Stir and serve over ice cream, cake or with a spoon (my favorite way).

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a skillet, brown meat with pepper and onion; pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients, except buns.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt butter. Mix dry ingredients. Add to butter. Beat well. Add eggs, beat well. Add nuts and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into shell. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken pizzaiola
directions: Arrange chicken, potatoes, peas, onion and mushrooms in a roasting pan.
Pour tomatoes over top.
Add salt, pepper, olive oil and cheese.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken divan
directions: Spread cooked broccoli on bottom of greased baking dish.
Top with chicken pieces.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry; spread on top of meat.
Top with cheese.
Melt butter; stir into crumbs. Spread crumbs on top.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Make pudding.
Add peanut butter.
Fold in half Cool Whip. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together and put on bottom of crust.
Then put pudding mixture in crust.
Put rest of Cool Whip on top.
Chill overnight.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by small spoonfuls into hot cooking oil.
Keeps good in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.
Serves 15.

title: key lime pie
directions: Grate lime rind; squeeze lime juice.
Hold, covered, for later use.
Soften plain gelatin in cold water.
Heat over hot water until gelatin is dissolved and clear.
Allow to cool to room temperature (but do not allow to gel).
Beat egg yolks until light and creamy.
Add condensed milk; continue to beat until light and well blended.
Add cooled gelatin mixture; continue beating until smooth.
Add lime juice, rind, vanilla and salt; beat until smooth and thickened.
Color should be very pale.
Place into prebaked pie shell.
Allow to chill and set for a minimum of 1 hour.
Top each pie with whipped topping or cream.
Leave cream rough on top. Garnish each piece with 1/4 lime slice.

title: scallops and artichokes on pasta
directions: Combine tomatoes, wine, oil, onions, garlic, parsley, Knorr seasoning, basil, sugar and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes or until onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until scallops are cooked.
Turn into ovenproof dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Broil until cheese is slightly brown.
Serve over noodles (vermicelli).

title: snoopy salad
directions: Marinate shrimp, celery and onions in Kraft dressing.
Cook the capellini according to directions.
Mix lemon juice, mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese together.
Toss pasta with shrimp mixture and mayonnaise.

title: roast salad for sandwiches
directions: Cook roast.
Grind roast, onions, eggs, pickles and peppers. Add mayonnaise to spreading consistency.
Keeps up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Serves 50.

title: squash casserole
directions: Pour all into buttered casserole dish.
Cover top with 1/4 cup stuffing.
Cook at 400° until brown on top.

title: best ever lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water in top of double boiler.
Add egg yolks with juice.
Beat. Add to rest of mixture.
Cook until thick, 25 minutes.
Add lemon extract, butter and vinegar.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: '57 chevy yum-yum bars
directions: Spread with nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Pour over the ingredients in pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm with a hot knife.
(Keep knife hot by dipping in hot water.)

title: slow cooker lasagna
directions: Brown meat. Drain. Mix with spaghetti sauce. Combine egg and cottage cheese. Layer half the ground beef mixture, half the dry noodles, half the cottage cheese mixture and half the Mozzarella cheese in the slow cooker. Repeat layers. Cover. Cook on high 4 to 5 hours or on low 6 to 8 hours. (I break my noodles so I can make sure they are completely covered with spaghetti sauce.) This is so easy and makes a delicious meal.

title: beef casserole(teenagers love this!)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, brown sugar and beans; heat until bubbly.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits; cut each biscuit in half crosswise.
Place biscuits cut side down around edge of casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Fry bacon and drain.
Set aside.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Mix all ingredients except bacon. Put in large bean pot and top with bacon.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: party pecans
directions: Melt butter in shallow 14 x 16-inch pan.
Beat egg whites, add sugar to make stiff meringue.
Add pecans, coat them in the meringue.
Place them in the buttered pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Stir 3 times during the baking process.
(Salt lightly when you put them in to bake.)

title: goldie's cream frosting
directions: Mix melted butter, vanilla and egg.
Add sugar alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.

title: chicken salad(serves 100)
directions: Cook chicken, adding salt, until

tender. Pick off bones and cut in bite size pieces. Don't use skin. Boil macaroni until tender, drain and rinse with cold water. Add chicken, celery, pineapple and grapes. Mix salad dressing, mustard and canned milk together and stir into other mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: taco pizza spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and dash of Worcestershire. Spread on a round pizza pan.
Add in following order:
taco sauce, taco dry seasoning mix, any toppings and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana split pie
directions: Thinly slice bananas; sprinkle with lemon juice and arrange on bottom of baked pastry shell.
Stir strawberry ice cream to soften slightly.
Spread ice cream atop bananas.
Freeze until firm. Spread thawed whipped dessert topping over ice cream.
Top with maraschino cherries; sprinkle with walnuts.
Freeze several hours or until firm.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and white sugar.
Mix together and freeze in loaf pan.

title: apple pie filling
directions: In a large saucepan, blend first 4 ingredients and 1 teaspoon salt.
Stir in 10 cups water; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add lemon juice and food coloring.
Pack apples into hot jars, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Fill with hot syrup, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Use spatula to help distribute syrup.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: bumpy pancakes
directions: Preheat griddle.
Finely chop apple.
Pour lemon juice over apple to prevent browning.
Beat together eggs, milk, butter, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Add bread cubes, apple and raisins.
Stir in baking powder.
Drop by spoonfuls or 1/4 cup dry measuring cup onto greased and preheated griddle.
Bake until small bubbles appear; then turn over and bake until golden brown. Makes approximately 1 dozen pancakes.

title: tuna dill sandwich
directions: Stir together the dressing, dill and pepper.
Add tuna, onion and carrots; mix well.
For each sandwich, top one muffin half with lettuce, cheese slice and tuna mixture.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: skillet pork chops
directions: Preheat skillet to 360° with 3 tablespoons oil.
Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Coat both sides with flour and brown. Remove chops and pour off excess fat.
Add water; bring to boil and pour liquid into cup and save.
Arrange rice evenly in bottom of skillet.
Pour evenly 1 1/2 cups or half of tomatoes over the rice.
Arrange onion slices over tomatoes.
Add chopped garlic. Pour other half of tomatoes over onion slices; add salt and black pepper.

title: holiday ham
directions: Trim off most of rind from ham.
Place ham in Dutch oven.
Add 6 cups of water, 1 cup of pineapple juice, 1 cup of Burgundy wine, half the brown sugar and cinnamon sticks.
Bring to a boil. Gently simmer for about 20 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate in liquid, covered, overnight, turning once in liquid.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, oleo and confectioners sugar; mix well. Press firmly into pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Combine eggs, lemon juice, sugar and baking powder; mix well.
Pour over crust. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Filling should be set, but not hard.
After the mixture cools, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: best corn bread
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix everything else together; pour into pan with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° until it is browned around the edges and set in the middle, about 35 minutes.

title: moon glow chicken
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Place chicken in, coating all pieces completely.
Cover bowl and marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: pasties("the old lumberjack hot sandwich")
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl, mixing well.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach; squeeze out excess water.
Mix well with other ingredients.

title: noodles
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Roll very thin on floured surface.
Let stand 20 minutes. Cook in boiling soup stock 10 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: May sprinkle grated cheese or bacon bits over dressing. Refrigerate up to 24 hours and serve.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix cookie crumbs and margarine and press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Pour filling into crust and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread, egg, onion, salt and pepper. Add sage and thyme.
Shape into 6 small loaves.
In skillet, brown loaves in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Stir in remaining soup, seasonings and water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until done.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.

title: luby's chopped steak
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into 3 or 4 fat patties.
Pan-fry, turning until beef is done.

title: german red kraut
directions: Melt Crisco in large pot.
Take off heat and add the ingredients.
Put back on stove and simmer until cabbage turns a blue color (1 hour), uncovered.
After cabbage turns, add hot water to cover cabbage.
Cook for 3 more hours on low heat, covered.
Test for taste.
Add sugar, salt or vinegar as needed. Never put vinegar directly on top of cabbage.
Put on side, then mix.

title: jelly doughnuts
directions: Combine warm milk, sugar, salt and margarine.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add milk mixture, eggs, whisk and 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add enough additional flour to make a stiff dough. Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 3 equal parts. Roll each piece into a circle 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 3-inch rounds, using top of glass.
Place on greased baking sheets; cover with dish towel.
Let rise in warm place free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: jan hagel
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a jelly roll pan.
Mix butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Mix thoroughly.

title: apple-cranberry drink
directions: To prepare oranges quickly, first peel and then cut across the equator.
All pits will be visible for picking out.
Put in blender; process at High speed until liquified.
Add the water. Wash the cranberries well in hot water and remove any stems.
Add to the blender; process at High speed until smooth.
Add the honey.
Wash and core, but do not peel, the apple; cut it into chunks, and blend at Medium speed until smooth again.

title: aunt pittypat's pecan pound cake(from the atlanta constitution, april 12, 1989)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs one at a time, beating until very smooth.
Sift flour, salt and nutmeg; add to sugar mixture alternately with sour cream and whiskey, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat just until well-blended; fold in pecans.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then turn out on a wire rack and finish cooling.
Pour glaze over cake. Decorate with pecan halves if desired.

title: taco dip
directions: Heat beans and spread evenly in dish.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning and spread over beans.
Sprinkle cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve with nachos.

title: fried rice
directions: Melt margarine in shallow skillet with lid.
Add onion and saute.
Add rice and fry, stirring frequently until has white porcelain appearance (do not brown).
Add crumbled chicken cubes and salt.
Stir well. Add water, stir well, cover and cook over medium heat until rice is tender (approximately 20 minutes).
Do not stir while rice is cooking.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lemonade-cider punch
directions: Combine lemonade concentrate with chilled cider instead of water.
Pour over ice ring or crushed ice in punch bowl.
Yields 36 servings.

title: mashed cauliflower
directions: Rinse and chop the cauliflower into about 1-inch pieces. Steam for 10 to 12 minutes. Put in blender with the same ingredients you would use with mashed potatoes. Blend until consistency is like mashed potatoes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: "quick and easy steak and pasta"
directions: Cook steak on medium heat in a large skillet with a small amount of water until tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Drain any liquid from steak and add tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix and spices to skillet.	Stir well and simmer on medium-low heat approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare pasta as directed on box.
Drain pasta and spoon steak sauce over bed of pasta on individual plates.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if desired.
Makes 4 large main dish servings.
Great with rolls and salad.

title: creamy vegetable medley
directions: In medium saucepan mix soup, milk, broccoli, carrots and cauliflower.
Over medium heat, heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break, cook and drain spaghetti. Mix all ingredients. Best to prepare the night before.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt. Add eggs, one at a time. Stir in melted margarine, milk and vanilla. Add pecans.
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion;
drain.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes over medium heat, uncovered.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then add beaten eggs, sour cream and margarine.
Mix all ingredients well, then add raisins.
Place in round pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind peppers, zucchini and onions.
Add pickling salt.
Let stand overnight.
Wash and drain.
