Combine all ingredients in kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Ladle into canning jars.
Seal in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Brown hamburger and add sauce. Simmer until heated.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheese.
Top with pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry upside-down cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle pan with marshmallows.
Combine flour, sugar, eggs, salad oil, salt, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Pour mixture over marshmallows. Mix gelatin with thawed strawberries and pour over cake batter. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken egg rolls
directions: Pour oil in wok, set on high.
Add celery, onions, and peppers and cook stirring constantly till slightly soft, (about 3 minutes).
Add water chestnuts, chicken, soy sauce and broth. Cook on medium high until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Stir often. Turn mixture on low and begin making egg rolls.
Look on back of egg roll package on how to roll them up.
Fry the egg rolls in hot oil in a fry cooker or skillet.
Place on paper towel to drain oil.
Serve immediately.
Should make 15 egg rolls.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together well cake mix, jello and flour.
Add oil, eggs and water.
Last add:
1 cup fresh or frozen, drained strawberries.

title: fiesta nacho dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix refried beans with taco seasoning mix in small bowl.
Spread mixture in bottom of 9x13 inch backing dish.
Arrange jalapenos atop bean mixture.
Spread sour cream atop jalapenos.
Sprinkle cheese atop sour cream.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly. Serve immediately with nacho chips.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Place apples and sugar in large bowl; let stand while preparing other ingredients. Separate eggs; beat egg whites until stiff and fold in egg yolks. Add cooking oil, beat well and let stand. In another bowl, mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon; stir in pecans. Pour egg mixture over sugared apples; add dry ingredients and stir. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Microcook potatoes on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes to finish cooking.
Cut potato in half lengthwise.
Scoop pulp into a medium bowl, leaving enough pulp inside shell to hold potato shape.
With a wire whip, beat hot potato until almost smooth.
Add butter and sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Add milk; stir in green onion and bacon.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Spoon mixture into potato shells, forming into mounds.
Place potatoes in shallow baking dish; sprinkle with cheese and microcook on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: new maryland crab cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In mixing bowl, beat egg until foamy. Beat in mayonnaise, mustard, onion, seafood seasoning and salt. Pick over crab; discard any bits of cartilage.
Add crab to egg mix.
Tear bread into pieces and process in blender to make coarse crumbs.
Add to crab mixture and mix gently by hand. Shape into ovals about 1 1/4-inches thick.
On baking sheet, smear oil in two ovals slightly larger than crab cakes, allowing 1/2 teaspoon oil per oval. Arrange crab cakes on oiled ovals.
Bake on middle shelf of oven 15 to 20 minutes or until crab cakes are dry on top and lightly browned.
Immediately run a broad spatula carefully under crab cakes to loosen them from baking sheet without tearing. Invert onto dinner plates with well browned bottom side up. Garnish with lemon wedges.
Makes 2 large cakes.

title: australian celery soup
directions: Stew celery in stock until very tender.
Add salt and nutmeg. Blend flour and milk and add, stirring constantly, while heating to boiling.
Do not boil.
Pour into soup cups and sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli ham roll-ups
directions: Cook broccoli.
Cook 3 cups white rice; lay in bottom of glass dish.

Place one stalk of broccoli at end of ham slice; roll. Place each broccoli/ham roll on top of rice until rice is covered. Melt Velveeta cheese and 3 tablespoons milk in microwave; pour hot sauce over dish.
Cook in microwave for 5 minutes on High or in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Everything is cooked, just warm through.

title: fruit dip
directions: Thaw lemonade; mix all. Refrigerate before serving.

title: linda's lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion together, drain excess fat.
Add tomato paste and tomatoes.
Cook in large saucepan for about twenty minutes, stirring all the time.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and shape in pan.
Mix the rest of ingredients and pour over meat loaf.

title: chocolate cheese cake pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: "jewish penicillin" - chicken soup
directions: In a large pot, place chicken.
Cover with water.
Add vegetables and seasonings. Cook until chicken is very tender and falls away from bones, 1 1/4 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain, then add sour cream and soup. Mix well.
Add to cooked noodles.
Pour in uncovered casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seashell salad
directions: Cook shells, drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine with all ingredients.
Chill well.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, milk, egg and oil.
Beat with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add squash, onion and red pepper and stir well.
Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into a hot, greased skillet.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Yield:
about 2 dozen.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and crumble in a large bowl.
Mix together soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put into buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: german skillet
directions: Layer ingredients.
Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add sauerkraut.
Sprinkle rice; add chopped onion to taste.
Break hamburger over all.
Spread tomato sauce over all.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not stir at any time.

title: beef balls sauterne
directions: Make meat balls of first 6 ingredients.
Brown in butter or margarine.
Remove meat balls.
Add green onion and celery to glaze.
Saute lightly.
Add mushrooms, water, bouillon cube, Sauterne, thyme and marjoram.
Thicken with flour mixed with a little water.
Add meat balls; heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix thawed and drained spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, onion and water chestnuts well. Refrigerate.
Cut a whole in center of loaf of bread.
Pull out bread, leaving the shell.
Cube bread.
Put dip inside bread shell.
Serve with cubed bread.

title: banana split dessert(must chill 6 hours before serving)
directions: Combine graham crumbs and 1 stick margarine.
Press into jelly roll or cookie pan.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 350°, making sure it doesn't scorch.
Cool.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Soften the cream cheese to room temperature.
Beat the sugar, cream cheese, vanilla and egg yolk together until fluffy.
Line the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with one can of crescent rolls.
(Smooth dough with fingertips.) Spread mixture in pan and top with the other can of crescent rolls.
Beat the egg white and spread over the top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until it appears baked.
Let cool.

title: chicken broccoli soup
directions: Cook chicken; chop chicken and save broth. Saut onion in 1/2 stick butter. Mix chicken broth, half and half, milk, onion, cheese, noodles, broccoli, salt and pepper in a large boiler. Stir frequently until cheese melts (about 20 minutes). DO NOT OVERCOOK; the mixture will curdle. If soup is too thick, add more broth, milk and half and half.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Place pork chops on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate town chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla, baking soda and salt with mixer.
Add flour; stir by hand.
Add one 12 ounce package of chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, cereal, cinnamon and margarine. Combine apples and raisins in baking dish.
Top with oat cereal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peppermint chiffon cake
directions: Set oven at 325°.
Flour 10-inch tube pan, 4 inches deep.
Do not grease pan.

title: shell salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease bottom of an 8-inch square baking pan.
In small bowl, mix together first 3 ingredients.
Stir in melted butter until well combined.
Reserve 1/3 cup crumbs.
Press remainder into pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Put layer of tortilla quarters on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat together soup, enchilada sauce, chili and garlic powders.
Top tortilla layer with about 1/3 of the cheese, 1/2 meat mixture and 1/2 the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining cheese.
Heat in 350° oven until cheese bubbles.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in shape of log.
Roll in paprika and wrap in foil.
Freeze.
Remove about 1 hour before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: onion and raisins
directions: Stew in tightly covered pot approximately 30 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until knife inserted comes out clean.
(Serves 6 to 8.)

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Drain and mash beans.
Melt butter and add to beans.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Mix well and pour into unbaked shells.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Prepare potatoes.
Drain hamburger.
Add tomato sauce.
Layer hamburger and sauce in casserole dish.
Layer corn on hamburger and potatoes on top of corn.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Tear meat apart with fork.
serve.

title: golden dream pie
directions: Arrange peach halves, cut side up, in pie shell.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Cut in butter.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes at 425°.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 35 or 40 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: overnight salad
directions: Mix and set in refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, add 1 cut up apple and 1 cut up banana.

title: white chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; set aside.
In separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking powder soda and salt.
Blend into butter mixture.
Stir in white chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: consomme rice
directions: Saute rice and onion in oleo.
Add mushrooms, beef consomme, water and salt.
Place in a casserole dish and cover with foil. Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: strawberry pecan cheese mold
directions: Combine all ingredients, except strawberry preserves, in a bowl.
Use only enough mayo to make ingredients stick together. Once mixed, place mixture in a mold of your choice (Bundt cake mold works nicely).
Allow to chill in refrigerator for several hours. Flip out of mild when ready to serve and cover lightly with strawberry preserves or place preserves in center opening as a dip. Serve with crackers.
Serves approximately 20 people.

title: strawberry slush punch
directions: Let frozen strawberries thaw and mix strawberries, orange juice and pineapple juice together.
Re-freeze mixture.
About 1 hour before serving punch, remove frozen mixture from freezer and partially thaw.
Cut into "chunks." Beat mixture with wire whip until broken up and "slushy."
Add ginger ale or 7-Up until punch is desired consistency.
Serve immediately.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into pieces and cook in salted boiling water until done al dente, 5 to 10 minutes.
Rinse in cold water and drain well.
Combine with celery, onion, pepper, mushrooms, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Chill overnight.
At serving time, garnish with olives, pepper rings and a goodly amount of chopped fresh parsley.
This salad keeps very well for several days.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let set in refrigerator overnight before baking.
Next morning, spray baking dish with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water until soft stage.
Stir in peanuts and cook to crackling stage.
Keep cooking; remove and add soda and salt.

title: scotch casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in 2 quarts salted water until tender.
Blend milk with soup; add meat, cheese, onion and garlic salt.
Blend well.
Grease casserole and fill with alternating layers of cooked macaroni with soup mixture.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.
May be made in 2 casseroles; bake one and freeze one for later.

title: lazy man pigs-in-a-blanket(low-fat)
directions: Spray a 3-quart casserole dish with cooking spray.
Spread a layer of chopped raw cabbage in bottom of casserole dish.
Place sliced potatoes on top of cabbage (use 1/2 of potato slices). Brown ground beef or turkey with onion until meat loses its color. Place a layer of meat on potatoes.
Spread 1/2 of spaghetti sauce on top.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cooper coins
directions: Heat sugar, tomato soup and cooking oil to boiling.
Cool 10 minutes and pour over carrots, onion and pepper.
Cover tightly and let stand overnight in refrigerator. These will keep for several days.

title: baked beans
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add onion and cook over medium heat.
Blend in ketchup, Tabasco, brown sugar and salt.
Bring to boil.
Add baked beans.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Cut bacon into pieces and put on top of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bacon is cooked.
Serve with hot rolls or bread.

title: golden nugget macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni per directions.
In a small frying pan, saute onion in margarine on medium-low heat until translucent.
Drain water from macaroni when done.
In same pot, add onion and remaining ingredients.
Heat over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until heated through.
Serve.

title: orange slush
directions: Make tea with tea bags and boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Freeze for 12 hours; stir thoroughly, then freeze for another 12 hours.
Spoon into glasses. Fill glasses half with 7-Up and serve.

title: delicious shower and wedding punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water on stovetop.
Blend bananas and strawberries together in blender.
Add these ingredients plus remaining in 1 large plastic container.
(Fits into 1 large Tupperware salad bowl.)
Freeze solid.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving or until mixture is slushy.
Add ginger ale to this in punch bowl.
Makes 2 punch bowls full.

title: susan's fruit cake
directions: Chopped nuts make it easier to mix.

title: my grandma's sweet potato cobbler
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in lengthwise slices.
Place in pot with just enough water to cover.
Stew for 15 minutes or until tender. With biscuit dough rolled into thin strips, grease sides of deep casserole dish and place strips of dough around sides.
Pour in half of the potatoes and juice and spread on top with 1 cup sugar, 1 stick butter and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Layer strips of dough across top, pouring remaining potatoes with juice.
Add 1 cup sugar, 1 stick butter and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla as before.
Cover with strips of dough sprinkled with 1/2 cup sugar.
Cut small piece of butter to place on top.
Cover with tinfoil and cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove tinfoil to brown top layer. Enjoy!!!

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water with salt.
After grits are cooked, add roll of garlic cheese.
Break cheese in pieces and add sticks of butter and eggs, well beaten.
Add milk and seasonings to taste.

title: sausage roll
directions: Mix hot roll mix according to directions on box.
Set aside to let rise.
Brown sausage and drain well.
Roll out dough and add sausage on top, then add cheese.
Beat egg adding just a little water.
Brush egg onto edges of dough.
Fold over edges and then roll up into a log.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: bacon buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and 2 tablespoons sugar in lukewarm water. Scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm. Add 2 cups flour to make batter. Add yeast mixture and eggs. Beat well. Add remaining flour or enough to make a soft dough.
Knead lightly and place in greased bowl. Cover and set in warm place free from draft.
Let rise until doubled in size, about 2 hours. When light, punch down and shape. Cook the bacon and onion until done.
Add a dash of pepper.
When cool, strain off excess bacon grease. Take a pinch of dough. Spread out flat by hand.
Put some bacon in open dough. Turn up sides and ends so all bacon is covered by dough and place on cookie sheet (greased). Dab milk over top of bacon buns. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or so.

title: inexpensive punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water.
Add orange juice and pineapple juice; mix.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: quiche alsacienne
directions: Brush pie shell with white of an egg and poke with fork.
Fry bacon, stirring constantly until fat almost all rendered out, but bacon isn't crisp.
Drain off fat.
Scald milk or cream; cool slightly.
Beat milk (or cream) with 4 eggs, salt, white pepper and sprinkle of nutmeg.
Sprinkle bottom of pie shell with bacon and sauteed onions.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375° or until top is golden brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oil and saute onions to wilt; lift out with slotted spoon to mixing bowl.
Soften tortillas in hot oil, keeping in only seconds or dip in salsa to soften.
Combine onions, chicken, olives and cheese.
Assemble and distribute chicken-cheese mix evenly onto the 12 corn tortillas.
Roll and place in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: rod's scalloped eggplant
directions: Pare and cube eggplant.
Cook in boiling salted (if desired) water for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Melt margarine and add flour; stir until blended.
Peel and chop tomatoes; add to above mixture. Chop onion and green pepper.
Add to above mixture along with brown sugar and salt.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Place eggplant in 2-quart greased baking dish.
Pour mixture over. Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla and pecans, in saucepan. Cook over medium heat to thread stage. Remove from heat; add vanilla, then add pecans. Stir until nuts are coated and mixture is creamy. Pour onto greased baking sheet. Separate with fork while cooling.

title: mel's new mexico chicken
directions: Lay chicken breasts flat and cut into strips 2-inches wide. Mix other ingredients together and melt in saucepan or microwave oven.
Cool and pour into plastic bag.
Place chicken into bag as well and shake to coat.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or prepare in the morning and refrigerate all day.

title: crunchy tossed salad
directions: In a jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper. Shake well until sugar is dissolved. Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: baba ghanouj
directions: Cut 1 inch slits in eggplant to prevent splattering while baking.
Bake at 500° until tender.
Split eggplant open and scoop inside pulp together with juice.
Mix tahini, garlic, lemon juice and salt to make sauce.
Add water if needed to make a thick sauce.
Add mashed eggplant.
Put in salad bowl and pour oil on top.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes (leave very thick).
Add garlic salt, 1 stick butter, sour cream, and cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients very well.
Put in casserole dish.
Use last stick of butter to cut into pieces and place on top of potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: In heavy bottomed pot or Dutch oven, lightly brown onion sprinkled with garlic powder in oil.
Add beef and brown.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper, and the next four ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer, uncovered for 30-40 minutes.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Combine rice and fruit in large bowl.
Pour pineapple juice over and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter, cocoa, sugar and evaporated milk together.
Bring to boil until smooth, not gritty.
Add vanilla and peanut butter. Melt; take off heat, then add oats.
Mix well.
Lay teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet, let cool and harden.

title: mama keen's salmon croquettes
directions: Melt butter over medium heat; stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk slowly and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in soft bread crumbs and salmon.
Chill several hours.
Shape into 8 croquettes.
Roll each lightly in flour, then dip in beaten egg and roll in dry bread crumbs.
Pour oil in skillet to a depth of 1-inch.
Heat to 390°.
Fry croquettes until golden (about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes) turning once. Drain on paper towel and keep warm.
Combine soup, lemon juice, cream and curry powder.
Heat until bubbly.
Serve with French bread and croquettes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cornflakes chews
directions: Heat corn syrup,
sugar
and
peanut butter in saucepan over low heat, stirring	until blended.	Stir in margarine and vanilla. Add cornflakes; mix well.	Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let stand	until
cool.
Store
in airtight container.

title: bride's maid salad
directions: Pit
cherries.	Dissolve
Jell-O.
Combine all ingredients, except
cream
and	mix well.
Fold in cream.
Place in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Stir well and put in refrigerator until set and firm.

title: chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: The cream cheese and butter need to be at room temperature. Place cream cheese and butter in a large mixing bowl. Blend with an electric mixer on low for about 30 seconds or until combined. Add cocoa, almond or vanilla extract and confectioners sugar. With mixer on low speed, blend about 30 seconds or until the ingredients are moistened. Increase mixer speed to medium and beat 2 minutes or until frosting is fluffy. Use at once to frost the top and the sides of the cake of your choice. Makes enough frosting to frost a 2 or 3 layer cake.

title: pickled summer squash
directions: Cover first five ingredients with cold water and let stand for 2 hours.

title: fresh peach muffins(from leadville country inn)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients.
Mix wet and dry ingredients until lumpy.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolk.
Mix dry ingredients and alternate with Pet milk, then add 2 cups milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Beat egg whites.
Put on pie and brown.

title: fried chimichangas
directions: Lightly brown hamburger; add onion, green pepper and garlic. Cook until onion is soft.
Stir in salt, cumin, chili powder, cayenne pepper and refried beans.
Cook until heated through.
Fold in cheese, let cool.
Place 1/4 filling in center of each shell. Fold one edge over filling, then fold in sides.
Starting from folded edge, roll up and secure with a toothpick (wooden).
Pour oil in frying pan over medium heat.
Add chimichangas and fry; turn.
Cook until golden brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Spoon salsa, guacamole, sour cream, etc. on chimis.
Ready to eat.

title: golden crumb broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Place in 3-quart baking dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes at 350°.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Put in a large kettle and cover with fresh water by 2 inches.
Bring slowly to a boil; reduce heat to simmer and cook gently until beans are almost tender.
Drain, saving the cooking water

title: celestial brownies
directions: Place oven rack in center of oven; heat oven to 375°.
Coat an 8-inch square baking pan with 1 tablespoon butter; reserve.
Melt chocolate with remaining 7 tablespoons butter; reserve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients.
Pour this over vegetables and chill.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar in double boiler.
Put into Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into pie shell or graham cracker crust. Garnish with dots of Cool Whip, nuts or slivers of chocolate.

title: aunt eve's cheese cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Add sugar and melted butter; mix well. Reserve 1 cup for top.
Chill crust in refrigerator while making filling.

title: company baked beans
directions: Drain beans and pineapple. Combine with remaining ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 or 12.

title: hot chocolate premix
directions: Mix together thoroughly and store.
Mix with water (hot or cold).
Add as much as you wish for flavor.
Great to make in early fall for the cold winter season.

title: salsa
directions: Peel, chop and seed tomatoes; allow to drain in a colander.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and flour.
Pour pineapple into greased casserole.
Pour egg mixture over pineapple; mix well.
Press bread cubes into the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Whip cream cheese and sour cream. Add potatoes and milk if needed.
Put in shallow pan and spread with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: coconut rolls
directions: Mix Rice Krispies and nuts in a bowl. Mix together rest of the ingredients, except vanilla, and boil 5 minutes, stirring all the time. Add vanilla. Pour over Rice Krispies and nuts and stir. Spoon out and roll in coconut. Lay on wax paper.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix well, but don't cook.
When cake is done baking and still hot, prick cake with a fork all over almost to bottom of pan. Then pour lemon juice mixture over the cake evenly.

title: physician services favorite crab dip
directions: Rinse and drain crab meat; put into a bowl.
Finely dice onion; add to crab.
Mix in cheeses, mayonnaise and seasonings. Cover and chill.
Serve with butter crackers.
Best if made the night before.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: blueberry cake or muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients (except sugar) together.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk, to egg mixture.
Mix all well.
Fold in blueberries. Before baking, sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and sugar (1 tablespoon cinnamon to 2 tablespoons sugar).
Bake for approximately 25 minutes or until tested done.
Yields 2 1/2 to 3 dozen cupcakes or 1 (9 x 13-inch) cake.

title: linguini and clams
directions: Heat oil to gentle boil and turn heat down.
Add parsley and garlic; heat thoroughly.
Add clams, salt and pepper and juice. Cook gently.
Cook linguini and drain.
Pour clam mixture over linguini.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; add enough buttermilk to make smooth paste.
Then add remainder of buttermilk.
Cook over hot water until thickened.
Then add egg yolks; cook a few minutes. Add butter, then cool.
Pour into one 8-inch or 9-inch baked pie shell.
Put meringue on pie and bake in slow oven (250°) about 25 minutes.

title: chicken in white wine
directions: Dice chicken into cubes and set aside.
Put oil into skillet pan and brown onion.
Add cubed chicken, mushrooms, salt, pepper and parsley to taste.
Add enough white wine to cover chicken. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or linguine.

title: fudge cake
directions: Bring to a boil the butter, water and buttermilk.
Sift together the flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add the eggs to chocolate mixture, then add dry ingredients.
Add the baking soda and vanilla; mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes in large pan.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda and add to above mixture.
Roll into balls the size of a small walnut and roll in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, but still soft.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: sour cream spice cake
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar thoroughly. Add egg yolks, bet thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together three times, add alternately with sour cream. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in greased pan 350 for 45 to 50 minutes

title: crispy oven-fried okra
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Trim off stem ends of okra and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Combine yellow cornmeal, salt and pepper in a medium bowl; stir mixture well and set aside.

title: cranberry mince pie
directions: Place rack in lowest position on oven; preheat to 425°.
In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; add water.
Over high heat, cook and stir to boiling.
Add cranberries; return to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Turn mincemeat into pastry lined pie plate.
Top with cranberries. Cover with vented top crust; seal and flute.
Brush with egg mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Pour all in a large bowl and mix.
Store in moisture-proof container.

title: lemon pie bars
directions: In an aluminum foil or Saran Wrap lined 8-inch flowerpot, layer cookies and filling over and over until you fill the pot.
Be sure to end with Oreos on top.
Place silk flowers in center, gummy worms hanging out of pot (optional).

title: no beans chili
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil. Add ground chuck and brown. Add remaining ingredients, cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar m&m's cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in half of M&M's.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Push M&M's into cookies and on top. Bake at 375° for about 7 minutes or until barely brown.

title: chewy cocoa brownies
directions: Stir together sugar, margarine and water in a large bowl. Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Combine cocoa, salt, flour and baking powder.
Stir dry ingredients into margarine and sugar mixture. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely and cut.

title: snack crackers
directions: Put crackers in largest paper grocery bag, doubled.
Mix oil and the rest of ingredients in medium bowl very well.
Pour over the crackers in the bag and shake real well.
Pour over on cookie sheets and let sit about 30 minutes.
Store in bags or bowls.

title: blueberry crush cake
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of pan.
Add blueberries and sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over blueberries.
Add cake mix and nuts. Mix the melted margarine with the 1/4 cup sugar.
Drizzle over cake mix.
Bake according to directions on box.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until crispy done.
Put in oiled casserole. Cover with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Melt oleo; dribble over crackers.
Heat thoroughly at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in butter along with the onions.
Arrange chicken in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients in pan used to brown chicken, simmering slightly to combine to make smooth sauce.
Pour over chicken. Bake in 400° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Can be made ahead of time but do not freeze.
Serve over long grain and wild rice.

title: ice cream pail pickles
directions: Boil.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Weigh down with a plate.
Leave on counter for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally. Put into jars and refrigerate immediately.
Keeps well.
These are great bread and butter pickles!

title: vegetable couscous
directions: In a large bowl, put 2 cups of whole wheat couscous.
Pour 4 cups boiling water over it and let sit at least 15 minutes.
Fluff with a fork and keep warm.
Saut onion and garlic in water until limp.
Add tomatoes and their liquid, carrots, celery, turnip, spices and honey.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Then add zucchini, red pepper, raisins, apricots and chickpeas.
Simmer for an additional 15 minutes.
Place couscous in individual soup bowls and top with the vegetable stew. Garnish with chopped mint or parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon-poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and 1 cup water in mixer bowl; mix well on low speed.
Beat at high speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm with whipped topping.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream the butter and the sugar.
Add vanilla, eggs, flour and chopped nuts and mix.
Grease and flour a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put 3/4 cup of the mixture in the pan and spread evenly.
Put cherry pie filling over the dough in pan.
Drop remaining dough over the top of pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size chunks.
Mix together cracker crumbs, cheese, basil and thyme.
Dip chicken into melted butter, then coat in crumb mixture.
Put in single layer in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden.

title: chicken fettucine with alfredo sauce
directions: Cut up chicken breast into cubes, brown and cook well.
In large saucepan melt butter on low (do not scorch).
Mix in 1 pint of heavy whipping cream and 2 eggs, slightly beaten.
Stir well then stir in Parmesan cheese, bring to a boil slowly.
In large pan cook broccoli, then noodles.
In large bowl, pour sauce mixture over chicken, broccoli.
Mix well then place over cooked noodles.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Scrape and trim the vegetables as necessary and wash them well. Separate the radicchio and endive into leaves.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix together and place salted chicken breasts on top of mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat slowly in butter.
Add onion and garlic last few minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water.
Add to meat.
Cover and simmer until almost tender. Add tomatoes and green pepper; cook 10 minutes.
Now combine cornstarch, cold water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat, bring to a boil and stir for 5 minutes.
Remove garlic.
Serve this over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: candy apples
directions: Insert a wooden ice cream stick partway through stem end of apples.
Grease large cookie sheet.
Set aside.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In cake pan, empty bag of Doritos and spread evenly.
In saucepan, dump both soups, enchilada sauce and dice up Velveeta. Cook until Velveeta is melted.
In skillet, brown hamburger.
Mix soups into hamburger; stir together.
Pour over the Doritos; spread evenly.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, then serve.

title: french fried cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower
into
flowerets.
Combine
flour and salt in a medium mixing bowl.
Combine
egg, milk and oil in a small mixing bowl.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Dip
cauliflower	into
batter.
Fry in deep, hot oil at 375°
until
golden.
Drain
on paper towels. Transfer to a serving
platter.
Serve
immediately.
Yields 6 to 8 servings or about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Store in tight container. Use 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Freeze separately on cookie sheet, then take as many as needed and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday cranberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine juice and grated rind of one orange.
Add Crisco with enough boiling water to make a total of 3/4 cup.
Add egg. Blend liquid with dry ingredients.
Stir just until flour is mixed.
(Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.)

title: seven layer salad
directions: Add ingredients, one at a time, in order given in a large bowl. Do not toss.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: sweet dills
directions: Use dill size cucumbers; soak in ice water for 3 or 4 hours. Heat sugar, 1 cup water, vinegar and salt.
Allow mixture to cool. Drain cucumbers; pack in jars.

title: english trifle
directions: In large bowl, slice part of cake into pieces to make layer. On top, drop strawberry pieces.
Cover with pudding.
Continue layering cake, strawberries and pudding until it is as large as you want.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut meat in small portions.
Combine flour, salt and pepper. Coat meat pieces and brown in hot oil in skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Add wine, water and undrained mushrooms, onion and parsley. Simmer covered for 1 1/2 hours until tender.
Add enough water to make 1 1/4 cups liquid.
Blend cornstarch in 1/4 cup water.
Stir in and cook until thickened.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: griddle cakes
directions: Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir well to mix. Combine milk, egg
and oil in bowl.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Grease
hot
griddle and pour batter for cakes.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, which have been beaten until lemon-colored.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon mixture into prepared 10-inch tube pan (the Bundt pan must be 10-inch or hold 12 cups, and angel food pan may also be used).
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Add glaze, if desired.
Cool in pan about 15 minutes before turning out.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil together.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Then add nuts, chips and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: mom's salmon cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into small cakes.
Dip into more cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides. Drain on paper towels and serve.

title: never-fail custard pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Slowly stir into eggs.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: taco twist
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce and green pepper.
Combine cooked macaroni with 1/2 cup cheese and sour cream.
Place in a 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Top with meat mixture and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: May use self-rising flour and omit soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then bananas.
Stir dry ingredients and add.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: good punch
directions: Stir together punch and pineapple juice.
Slowly add 7-Up.

title: great cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in iron skillet.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add melted butter and stir.
Pour into hot iron skillet.
Bake 30 minutes or until center is done.

title: pineapple and banana cake
directions: Blend these ingredients with enough confectioners sugar to thicken to right consistency to spread.
This is a very moist delicious cake.

title: baked venison steaks
directions: Brown steaks in margarine in skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Blend soup and water until smooth.
Arrange steaks in greased baking dish and add layers of onions.
Add half the soup. Repeat layers, ending with soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until steaks are tender.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Add flour, soda and salt into this mixture.
Fold in quick oats, then corn flakes, then pecans and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Freezes well.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Stir in combined dry ingredients, vanilla, chocolate and nuts.
Roll into balls; place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce for canning(7 pints)
directions: Combine oil, pepper and onion.
Cook onion until transparent. Add all other ingredients, except sugar.
Cook sauce 2 1/2 to 3 hours, adding the sugar the last hour of cooking.
Pour hot sauce into hot jars and seal.
May also put into containers and freeze.

title: micro apple-kraut relish
directions: Drain and rinse sauerkraut well.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes on High.
Stir before serving.

title: eggplant cheese casserole
directions: Dip eggplant slices in mixture of egg and water.
Saute in oil.
Drain.
Cook beef and onions in remaining oil until onions are golden brown.
Remove fat.
Add tomato sauce and spices. Layer meat sauce, eggplant and cheese in a 2-quart casserole, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ramp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve with your favorite dressing.

title: nutritious shake
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend for about 20 seconds or	until
the
shake
is
smooth and frothy.
Makes 4 servings, 133 calories per serving.

title: chop suey
directions: Heat oil and brown pork and veal lightly.
Add onion, brown lightly.
Stir in flour, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat.
Cover and cook 1 hour.
Add celery and mushrooms and cook 15 minutes more.
Add bean sprouts, soy sauce and water chestnuts during last 5 minutes of cooking.
Serve over rice. Serves 6.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add flour and salt.
Chill until firm enough to handle.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in large bowl. Mix well. Pour half of mixture into greased 10-inch iron frypan.
Top with cheese and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 450° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: irish potato soup
directions: In large pot, bring broth, potatoes, onions and salt to boil. Simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
With potato masher or wooden spoon, coarsely mash potatoes in broth.
Add whipping cream and parsley. Heat 5 minutes and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chile verde
directions: Brown about 1/4 of meat at a time.
Remove with slotted spoon. Saute bell pepper and garlic, adding more oil if needed.
In 5-quart kettle, combine tomatoes, including juice, chiles, garlic, seasonings and wine.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer. Add browned meat and sauteed vegetables; cover and simmer at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove cover and continue to simmer 45 minutes longer or until sauce is thickness desired and meat is tender.
Seres 6 to 8.

title: vegetable "relish" salad
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil.
Let cool.
Combine vegetables in large bowl with cover.
Pour dressing over all.
Let set overnight in fridge before serving.

title: hamburger soup (or turkey)(great!)
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain well.
Combine all ingredients, except pasta, in large pot.
Cover and simmer at least 2 hours or all day.
Put pasta in 1 hour before serving.
Serve with salad and crusty bread.
Serves 10.

title: biscuits
directions: Pour flour into a bowl and cut in shortening.
Add mix. Mix just enough to blend.
Pour out on floured board and knead several times.
Roll
out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutters. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sherry's jellied cherry cups
directions: Drain cherries, reserving syrups.
Combine syrups with lemon juice.
Add water to make 3 1/2 cups liquid.
Bring to a boil and pour over gelatin.
Stir to dissolve.
Chill until partially set. Add cherries and nuts.
Shape cream cheese into marble sized balls. Add to gelatin and pour into mold(s) until set.
Unmold and serve as individual salads or as whole.

title: quick-y broccoli benedict
directions: Place unopened broccoli pouch in vigorously boiling water. Do not cover.
Heat for 18 minutes.
In small bowl, combine broccoli and mustard.
Place ham on split, toasted muffin and top with broccoli mixture.
Garnish with egg.
Serves 2.

title: microwave lasagne layered with spinach(serves 8)
directions: (Takes only 20 minutes to assemble!)
To begin sauce, put butter in a 2-quart glass bowl, cover with lid or plastic wrap and microwave on High until the butter is melted.
Add onion, garlic and mushrooms and toss them until they are coated with butter. Cover bowl again and microwave on Medium High (70% power) for 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, reserved tomato juice, tomato paste, wine, oregano, basil, sugar, salt and some pepper.
Stir well.
Cover bowl with a paper towel and microwave contents on High for 12 minutes, stirring every 4 minutes.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and set mixture aside.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with spatula dipped in flour.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly, then roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen small cookies.
(You may want to double the recipe.)

title: italian rice pudding
directions: Cook rice from directions on the box; add butter and cool. When rice is cool, add all remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into two 9 x 13-inch glass oven dishes and bake at 350° until knife comes out clean when testing.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate until served. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peas and mushrooms
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in a pot with 1/4 cup water.
Bring it to a boil, lower heat and simmer until peas are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all ingredients until moistened, then beat with mixer 2 minutes.
Pour into 6 greased and floured loaf pans (small ones). Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: baked fruit
directions: Drain all canned fruit.
Grate the rind of lemon and orange; peel and slice.
Layer lemon and orange slices and other fruit in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine lemon and orange rind, brown sugar and flour; mix well and sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts in the oil; cut into small pieces and drain.
Place one pie crust in pan; fill with chicken, mixed vegetables and potato soup.
Pour whipping cream over top.
Cover with remaining pie crust.

title: syrup pie
directions: Add all ingredients to well beaten eggs.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix milk, pineapple and enough orange drink to fill container of electric ice cream freezer.
Freeze as you would any homemade ice cream.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix meal, flour and salt.
Melt shortening over medium heat in a 9-inch iron skillet.
Add buttermilk to meal mixture, then add shortening.
Stir.
This needs to be a thick pouring consistency. Add more buttermilk, if needed.
Pour into hot skillet and bake in hot 450° oven until brown.
Break corn bread into pieces in large bowl.
In medium saucepan, put chopped celery and onion.
Cover with water and cook until tender, then pour over corn bread (do not strain).
Mix and add sage, chicken broth and chicken gravy.

title: salad nicoise
directions: Early in day:
Cook potatoes and eggs; refrigerate. Forty-five minutes before serving:
In small bowl, mix well, olive oil, vinegar, salt, tarragon and pepper; set aside.
Arrange vegetables over lettuce in large platter.
Spoon dressing over individual salads.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown and drain beef and turkey and simmer with spaghetti sauce.
Add mushrooms, onions, salt and oil.
Layer half the noodles, Ricotta, Mozzarella and sauce in lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle lightly with oregano and basil; repeat layers and sprinkle top with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: apple torte
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt; add to first mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve with scoop of ice cream on the side or whipped topping on top.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Mix well.
Put in 2-quart casserole and top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon dill potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly with a brush.
Pat dry.
Prick potatoes with a fork.
Bake in a 425° oven for 40 to 60 minutes, or until tender.
Or, microcook, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 14 to 17 minutes, or until almost tender, rearranging once. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Gently scoop out each potato half, leaving a thin shell (because potatoes are hot, you may want to hold the potato halves with a pot holder while scooping).
Place potato pulp in a large bowl.
Add 3 tablespoons of the melted margarine or butter, sour cream, dill or dill weed, lemon juice, garlic salt and pepper.
With an electric mixer on low speed, beat until smooth.
Pile the mixture into the potato shells.

title: coast guard bean soup
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight.
Discard water before proceeding.
Cook presoaked beans, ham hocks and bay leaves in chicken stock about 1 1/2 hours (until al dente).
Saute together onion, garlic, carrots, celery, leeks and tomatoes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Sift dry ingredients twice.
Add beaten egg, mixing with fork until crumbs form.
Sprinkle over fruit
(apples or peaches are best).
Sugar may be added to fruit before it's put into baking dish.
Melt butter.
Pour over top. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: howdy neighbor cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix. Sprinkle bottom of pan with coconut and almonds (1/4 cup of each).
Add 1 cup coconut almond mixture to batter and stir in.
Sprinkle remainder of coconut almond mixture over top of batter. Sprinkle cinnamon nutmeg mixture over top. Bake according to cake directions.
It's good enough to carry over to the neighbors.

title: sour cream peach pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.	Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach in large pan; drain and add all other ingredients to spinach.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
24 small balls.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and chop onions.
Cook for 5 minutes in salt water, drain.
Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots and fold in squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix and butter together.
Spread half in bottom of baking dish (12 x 7 x 2-inch).
Pour squash, onion, carrots, soup and sour cream mixture on the stuffing, then put the rest of stuffing on top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Melt butter; saute onion until golden brown.
Add soup, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Combine noodles, soup mixture and corned beef.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
